Now onto the apps, let’s start with games. The game that I have been currently

00:01:04,639 --> 00:01:07,799
a lot of YouTubers were talking about it,
so I thought, huh, I better go

free, if you were wondering,

20
00:01:12,159 --> 00:01:17,979
And it is so cute! I fell in love with it,
I’m addicted, I play it every day.

21
00:01:17,979 --> 00:01:22,920
And even though I’m slower at video games…
I’m slow, but you know what it’s so cute.

22
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:27,979
You start here at level 1, and then as you
complete the levels, you move through

23
00:01:27,979 --> 00:01:31,009
the world dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh!

24

Level 38, I’m here in the North Pole, it’s

25
00:01:35,409 --> 00:01:38,899
Your little bug characters are trying to make
their way home to Mount Boom,

26
00:01:38,899 --> 00:01:44,039
where their friends and family are, and you’re
defeating evil slugs.

27
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:47,680
Look at these little bugs, they’re so cute,
because you can level them up,

28
00:01:47,689 --> 00:01:51,380
and you unlock the characters as you're moving
through the levels, my favorite little

29

And let me show you what a level looks like.

00:01:58,999 --> 00:02:03,029

00:02:07,739 --> 00:02:12,260

see his health bar is right up above and

then you’re gonna connect, you can do all
these diagonals, deals damage to the

35

slug, dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh-dig-uh doom!

You can also connect to the game through Facebook

00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:25,670
have gotten. You do not need an iPhone to
download this game, it’s available

38
00:02:25,670 --> 00:02:30,629
on iPhone, iPad and Android. Alright, so that is the
game that I am playing and I’ll

39
00:02:30,629 --> 00:02:34,629
put a link down below to everywhere that you
can download it, I personally love

40
00:02:34,629 --> 00:02:37,799
this game, but I am warning you, it’s addictive!

41
00:02:37,799 --> 00:02:42,049
Now, I’m gonna show you some of my favorite
educational apps.

42
00:02:42,049 --> 00:02:45,849
The first app I’m gonna show you is the
one I use the most, I use it every night

43
00:02:45,849 --> 00:02:49,769
to listen to books on tape before I go to
bed, and when I’m traveling.

44
00:02:49,769 --> 00:02:52,989
It’s really good for when you're traveling and you want

45
00:02:52,989 --> 00:02:55,689
sometimes you can fit in 2 books, and that
app is Audible.

46
00:02:55,689 --> 00:02:59,010
For those of you who aren’t familiar with
Audible, it is an app where you can

47
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:03,069
download audio books and listen to them. And
if you’re like me and you have

48
00:03:03,069 --> 00:03:07,159
difficulty reading, sometimes it’s really
helpful, I like to buy the physical copy of

49
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:11,459
the book, and then I listen along to Audible,
I went to twitter and I asked

50
00:03:11,459 --> 00:03:16,930
you guys what book I should check out and I got so many suggestions, and 1 of them was the uglies series.

51
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:20,769
And that really intrigued me, so I looked it up,
and I got the book, and it’s a 4 part

52
00:03:20,769 --> 00:03:25,170
series, set in a dystopian world. The first
book is called Uglies, and then theres

53
00:03:25,170 --> 00:03:28,749
Pretties, Specials and Extras, and this book
is written from the perspective of

54
00:03:28,749 --> 00:03:32,900
Tally, she’s the main character and she

55
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:38,989

56
00:03:38,989 --> 00:03:44,230
Once you’re Pretty you enter the bigger
society and the idea behind that is everyone

57
00:03:44,230 --> 00:03:48,959

And then the Specials are basically

58
00:03:48,959 --> 00:03:53,079

they run faster, their bones

59
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:56,159
don’t break. Extras, I don’t even know
what those are, I haven’t made it there

60
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:59,540
yet. I’ve really been enjoying this book,
so if you would like to check out Audible,

61
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:04,209
or read this book, you can go to  Audible.com/RosannaPansino, and you will get

00:04:04,209 --> 00:04:09,909

teach myself Italian…. Hahahahaha.

I’m laughing because I’m a slow learner
but, I’m working, I’m working on it.

66
00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:29,680
I wanted to learn Italian for 2 reasons, 1
is because I wanted to tap into my

67

in Southern Italy, and when

68

so I thought it would be really

Also, I’ve been singing a lot of

71

Opera lately and my voice coach recommended

00:04:50,970 --> 00:04:54,930

love and I’ve been messing around with.

So, the little app for Duolingo is that cute
little green face. You just tap

title: What's on Bailey's iPhone | Brooklyn and Bailey
description:
Come along with us to see what Bailey has on her iPhone 6 , and be sure to click below to download Best Fiends for FREE!  http://download.bestfiends.com/ 
_

A few months ago, we posted Brooklyn's "What's On My iPhone" video! You guys loved it, so we filmed another one but for my (Bailey) iPhone! We are super appreciative to Best Fiends for partnering with us on this special phone tour video for y'all! 

Since we've worked with Best Fiends before, they decided to hide a treasure especially for OUR FANS in the game! It's our B&B logo, and you can find it vial the clue, "Even as twins, we're not always speaking the same language"! Go see if you can find our hidden treasure!

Brooklyn is way more organized than I am, but today you'll get a deeper look into my personality by seeing what apps I keep on my iPhone, including those that I use the most! 

We do spend a lot of time on our YouTube and social media apps, as well as our CuteGirlsHairstyles app. I also love my scriptures app for early morning seminary and for at Church, and my Kindle app for recreational reading. I love to edit photos, so I go through my favorite app for that as well one that I use to track fashion trends. I only have one game on my phone... can you guess what it is??? Best Fiends!

💥SUPERFANS💥: Please help us translate this What's on Bailey's iPhone video, and get credit below! http://www.youtube.com/timedtext_video?v=prd9TIwQ038&ref=share

If you loved this iPhone tour video, be sure to give it a HUGE "👍🏻" and please leave a comment below telling us what level of Best Fiends you are on! I am now on level 67!

❤️'s -Bailey
Don't forget to get our NEW merch, too! http://www.brooklynandbailey.com/shop
_

Don't forget to subscribe to our YouTube channel...
http://www.youtube.com/user/BrooklynAndBailey?sub_confirmation=1

Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/BrooklynAndBailey
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/BrookAndBailey
Instagram: http://www.Instagram.com/BrooklynAndBailey
Follow us on SnapChat: @BrookAndBailey

_

FTC Disclaimer: This video is sponsored by Best Fiends.

title: Top 5 AMAZING DIY Slimes from Instagram!!! Oddly Satisfying ASMR Compilation
description:
♥ NEW!!! 10 Easy 5-Minute Crafts To Do When You're BORED! ♥ https://youtu.be/o6xwfezESTQ
♥ Download Best Fiends for FREE!! Apple & Android ♥ http://download.bestfiends.com/forever - This video is sponsored by Best Fiends
IG SLIME LOVERS where u at! Learn how to make DIY Clear Slime, Deco Slime, Avalanche Slime (name created by @honey.guts Instagram), Dippin Dots Slime, Pearly Slime and Glitter Slime with NO borax, detergent or liquid starch.
♥ DIY Giant Rainbow Slime ♥  https://youtu.be/jAa43sKklfg
♥ SUBSCRIBE to my second DIY Craft Channel CUTE LIFE HACKS! ♥  https://www.youtube.com/cutelifehacks
Many people have requested an ASMR slime DIY so I hope you'll enjoy this!! I've been following lots of DIY slime Instagram accounts and began noticing many "new" slime styles pop up. These include using foam balls, mixing clear DIY slime with white DIY slime, pearly effects or adding polymer clay cane slices.

Of course you CAN substitute borax solution for the contact lens liquid. If you do that, you can skip the baking soda as well. (Baking soda is used to create alkaline pH conditions in the glue. This "activates" the sodium borate inside eye drops or contact lens solution which causes the PVA to clump together, thus creating slime. So you've effectively "made" borax using baking soda and eye drops...which is why these two things need to be used together in DIY slime recipes)

♥ Useful DIY Tutorial Links ♥
DIY Nail Polish Remover Slime: https://youtu.be/2Q5MVSK9Afg
DIY Crystal Slime: https://youtu.be/-Jj2omKnT6w
DIY Fluffy Slime: https://youtu.be/7gh4_teGvfUvfU

♥ DIY Shopping Links ♥
Tiny Plastic Pots for Slime: http://amzn.to/2ez9qjo, http://amzn.to/2ek8hQK, http://amzn.to/2euqb2W
Elmers Clear PVA Glue: http://amzn.to/2eOTEn1
Elmers White PVA Glue: http://amzn.to/2dpnKbC
Baking Soda: http://amzn.to/29SxhWK
Contact Lens Solution: http://amzn.to/2arGBmg
Food Colouring: http://amzn.to/29SxdpY
Fruit Cane Slices: https://goo.gl/S3Texv, https://goo.gl/gNosl4, https://goo.gl/eJ2xjX, https://goo.gl/m5e4YC
Lustre Dust: http://amzn.to/2dyCloh
Styrofoam Balls: https://goo.gl/IIymlU
Iridescent Glitter: http://amzn.to/2dpnpG1
*I've only included Amazon USA links since that's where the majority of my viewers are. However you can simply search for the same item or brand on your local Amazon(s) and most should be able to ship.

ASMR stands for "Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response" and basically means those quiet Youtube videos that are relaxing to listen to.

♥ Snapchat Username ♥ @maqaroon
♥ Instagram ♥ http://instagram.com/maqaroon
♥ Cute Life Hacks Channel ♥ http://www.youtube.com/cutelifehacks
♥ My Hamster Channel ♥ http://www.youtube.com/fluffieland
♥ Facebook ♥ http://www.facebook.com/maqaroon
♥ Twitter ♥ http://twitter.com/Maqaroon
♥ Tumblr ♥ http://maqaroon.tumblr.com/

(c) Joanna Zhou 2016
Contains Music from Epidemic Sound (http://www.epidemicsound.com)
Video sponsored by Best Fiends
Dieses Video entstand in Zusammenarbeit mit Best Fiends
Contains affiliate links

The brands of clear glue that definitely work for DIY slime are Elmer's Glue (USA), Povinal (Asia), Pelikan Pelifix (Germany, Austria), AMOS (Korea, USA) and Pritt Craft Glue (UK). These are just the countries I know of, so they may well be sold in other places too! Trying searching each brand online and you'll be able to see if the deliver to you. I bought my eye drops form Pearle Optik and the contact lens solution and facewash from DM.

We CUT OPEN a VINTAGE 1980 PACMAN MACHINE!?!

Let us know in the comments if you got to level 100 before Lincoln! Every 50 levels after 100 there are new magical character quests where you can win exciting and exclusive prizes like gold.

This Pac-man, Ms. Pac-man game was so much fun! They aren't as hard to find as you might think. Vintage Arcade Machines are everywhere for sale, people just don't think about it as much these days.

I had the pleasure to work with Best Fiends for this video! I decided to paint the land of Minutia along with some of my favourite fiends. They're having a well deserved rest and fun time after freeing their families and the rest of Minutia from the slug pest that took over after the meteorite struck Mount Boom. 

Temper is so mesmerized by that strawberry and the whole strawberry patch. Bob is having fun seeing how entranced his fiend is. Kwincy is rejoicing in the scent of mellow flowers while Labbit is overly eager because he can see home from the top of the tree. Howey is waiting for the rest to be ready to start their journey back home, now as heroes and best fiends.

title: Video Games Cause Aggression?
description:
This video was sponsored by Best Fiends 

Click here to download Best Fiends for FREE: http://download.BestFiends.com/AprilPromo

Welcome to the first edition of Psych News, where we announce new discoveries in the world of Psychology and human behavior. Todays stories include:

0:10 The effects of video games on aggression

Ever since the rise of violent media in TV, movies, and now video games, their effects on kids and society have been hotly debated. A number of studies have concluded that the effects of video games on individuals are generally negative. Generally people who play violent video games show an increase in aggression and a decrease in empathy. Though video game effects seem to be largely negative, a current study decided to further expand on the findings. Previous work done on the social effect of video games have been examined from a short term perspective. This new study examined video game effects in the long run and concluded there may be good effects of video games. 

2:44 New watch tells you if you're a boring conversationalist 

Scientists have finally developed a watch that can determine a conversations tone. Using audio, text transcriptions, and physiological signs this watch can determine a conversations tone with 83% accuracy. Researchers say this is most helpful for those with anxiety or aspergers because it acts like a social coach. 


Voice Over by Donna (Psych IRL): https://www.youtube.com/user/DesigningDonna

Animation by: Emma Schrederis https://vimeo.com/e94

More Psych2Go here: http://youtube.com/psych2go
Website: http://psych2go.net
Twitter: http://twitter.com/psych2go
Facebook: http://facebook.com/psych2go
Tumblr: http://psych2go.me

title: What's on Brooklyn's iPhone  | Brooklyn and Bailey
description:
Come along with us to see what Brooklyn has on her iPhone 6 , and be sure to click below to download Best Fiends for FREE!  http://download.bestfiends.com/ 
_

One of our most-requested videos this past year has been a "What's On My iPhone" video! We are super appreciative to Best Fiends for partnering with us on this special phone tour video for you! 

In today's video, you'll get a deeper look into my personality by seeing what apps I keep on my phone, including those that I use the most! I am super picky in how I organize my apps in folders, and love that everything is usually only 1 click away from the home screen.

We do spend a lot of time on our YouTube and social media apps, as well as our CuteGirlsHairstyles app. I also love my scriptures app and my Kindle app. I only have one game on my phone... can you guess what it is??? Best Fiends!

Be sure to subscribe, because Bailey will be doing a "What's on my iPhone" video sometime in the near future!

💥SUPERFANS💥: Please help us translate this What's on Brooklyn's iPhone video, and get credit below! http://www.youtube.com/timedtext_video?ref=share&v=k1AuzB7kNAY

If you loved this iPhone tour video, be sure to give it a HUGE "👍🏻" and please leave a comment below telling us what level of Best Fiends are you on! I am now on level 35!

❤️'s -Brooklyn


Don't forget to subscribe to our YouTube channel...
http://www.youtube.com/user/BrooklynAndBailey?sub_confirmation=1

Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/BrookAndBailey

Follow us on SnapChat: @BrookAndBailey

00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,740

00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,500
Ok, here I am

3
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:19,760
Hello Frogs and Toads and welcome to this new and amazing GamePlay, I'm Fraffrog

4
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:28,900
And today I'm here to try this brand new game called Best Fiends. You can download it directly onto your smartphone

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
In fact I have it right in front of me, so now LET'S PLAY

6
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:34,300
It's a really fun game and you can do many things

7
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:38,160
The goal is to form a long chain with these objects

8
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,800
In order to defeat the black snails aka "Sluggs"

9
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,240
SO.. let's begin with level 1

10
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:46,640
What the...??

11
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:52,880
Fraffrog, there's no time. Please help us!!

12
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:54,720
What?!

13
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:57,220
I can't explain right now. Do you know what to do?

14
00:00:57,220 --> 00:00:58,100
Emm.. No!

15
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,420
Very well! Be ready to fight then!

16
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:03,500
What are you talking about??!!! You came here from nowhere, without no explanation!

17
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:07,000
I don't even know if you're just an hologram made by my phone and... Now What?!

18
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,000
IT'S COMIIIING!!!

19
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,840
nbrbhurihbnuirenb *random noises*

20
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:16,120
Well... Hello Mr. Evil Slugg and Welcome.

21
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:20,500
If you could give us a moment, I have something to discuss with my collegue here. Thanks

22
00:01:21,820 --> 00:01:27,500
Forget the apparition, forget the fact that I don't how I'll explain this to my phone's client assistance

23
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:30,580
But now, tell me, WHY are you here? WHAT do you want from me?

24
00:01:30,580 --> 00:01:32,700
The Sluggs attacked Minutia falling from a meteor

25
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,420
With the less amount of words you are capable of

26
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,860
KILL HIM!

27
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,280
Him?!

28
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:37,940
Yes!

29
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,000
But he didn't do anything!

30
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:40,960
He's eating your computer!!

31
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
THEN HE DESERVES TO DIE!!

32
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:46,140
You, little thing, tell me what to do!

33
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:49,900
You have to link together as many objects of the same type as possible , like in the game

34
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:50,600
How can I do that?

35
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,100
With your finger, pretend that you're actually using your phone

36
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,160
WHAT?! He's bigger than before!

37
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,860
You have to make a far bigger chain if you want to destroy him

38
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,500
You have to find something really numerous

39
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:23,300
Ok, listen, I don't care. Eat whatever you want. You: are on your own. Bye. Adios

40
00:02:23,460 --> 00:02:27,500
Wait. Please! Try to focus. You have to find something REALLY numerous

41
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:30,160
Otherwise the whole world will be in great danger!

42
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,520
*think think think*

43
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,000
By the power of the Coffee!

44
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,820
Perfect, good work. Byebye

45
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,040
You're welcome!!

46
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:58,720
What?

47
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,500
It is still recording?!

48
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:08,860
Hello Frogs and Toads and Thank you for watching this video

49
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:11,800
I remind you that if you'd like to buy this game you could find it in the description box of this video.

50
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:14,500
I send you a hug and a little tender pat.

51
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,000
BYE!

52
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,460
No, no, no.. I'll never do a Game Play again. Too much labor

53
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:29,820
Created by Fraffrog

54
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:32,040
Subscribe

55
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,920
Last video

title: DIY PANDA TREATS!
description:
Special thanks to Best Fiends, WWF and Apple for sponsoring this video.

Play Best Fiends Free: http://download.BestFiends.com 

Today I made three different Panda themed treats! I hope you enjoy them. Thank you to Best Fiends for collaborating and sponsoring this video #sponsored!

ORDER MY BAKING LINE: http://bit.ly/BakingLine

For more information about #AppsforEarth visit http://appstore.com/appsforearth

FOLLOW ME:
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/rosannapansino
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/RosannaPansino
Tumblr: http://www.rosannapansino.tumblr.com
Instagram: http://instagram.com/rosannapansino
Snapchat: rosannapansino

THE THINGS YOU WILL NEED:
Panda Macarons
Cookies:
* (3/4) Cup Powdered Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCy8v
* (1/2) Cup and (2) Tablespoons Almond Flour: http://amzn.to/1W7lqbN
* (2) Egg Whites
* (1/4) Cup Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCAgA
* (1) Container Black Food Coloring Dye: http://amzn.to/1r3yDr6
Filling: 
* (1/2) Cup Heavy Cream
* (1) Cup White Chocolate Chips: http://amzn.to/1W7ltEp
* (2) Decorating Bags: http://amzn.to/1r3yK62
* (1) #2A Decorating Tip: http://amzn.to/1NfiCb6
* (1) #5 Decorating Tip: http://amzn.to/1NfiFUj

Panda Panna Cotta
* (1) Cup Milk
* (1-1/2) Cup Heavy Cream
* (1) Cup Greek Yogurt
* (6) Tablespoons Water
* (3/4) Cup Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCAgA
* (2) Packets Powdered Gelatine: http://amzn.to/1r3A1de
* (1) Teaspoon Vanilla Extract: http://amzn.to/1r3A4FM
* (1) Teaspoon Almond Extract: http://amzn.to/1r3A88L
* (1) Bag White Candy Melts: http://amzn.to/1r3A9cz
* (1) Bag Black Candy Melts: http://amzn.to/1W7mE72
* (1) 1/2 Sphere Silicone Mold: http://amzn.to/1XBDjhZ
* (1) Cup and (2) Tablespoons Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCAgA
* (1/2) Cup All Purpose Flour: http://amzn.to/1QepdwU
* (1/3) Cup Dark Cocoa Powder: http://amzn.to/1Qepf8c
* (1/3) Cup of Whole Milk
* (1/2) Cup Vegetable Oil: http://amzn.to/1QephwM
* (1) Egg
* (1) Teaspoon Vanilla Extract: http://amzn.to/1r3A4FM
* (1/3) Teaspoon Salt: http://amzn.to/1Qepjol
* (1/4) Teaspoon Baking Powder: http://amzn.to/1XBDpWT
* (3-1/4”) Circle Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/1QeptMq

Panda Pudding Cups
* (1) Box Oreos: http://amzn.to/1XBDCt0
* (4) Small Dessert Cups: http://amzn.to/1W7nBMz
* (2) Cups Whole Milks
* (1/3) Cup Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCAgA
* (3) Tablespoons Corn Starch: http://amzn.to/1XBDJoz
* (2) Pinches Salt : http://amzn.to/1Qepjol
* (2) Tablespoons Butter
* (1/2) Vanilla Bean: http://amzn.to/1W7nIrj
* (1) Cup Heavy Whipping Cream
* (2) Tablespoons Sugar: http://amzn.to/1XBCAgA
* (1) Bag Black Candy Melts : http://amzn.to/1W7mE72
* (1) 1 Ounce Ice Cream Scoop: http://amzn.to/1NfjY5I
captions:
1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:04,700
Hey guys, it’s Ro! As many of you know,
I love the game Best Fiends,

2
00:00:04,710 --> 00:00:10,179
I play it a lot! Someone may be on level 414….

3
00:00:10,179 --> 00:00:14,079
I love the character Howie, it’s my favorite
character, last time I showed you guys

4
00:00:14,079 --> 00:00:18,619
he kind of looked like an apprentice, like a mage,
and he had little magic balls,

5
00:00:18,619 --> 00:00:22,259
and now, I have leveled him up the highest
you can go right now!

6
00:00:22,259 --> 00:00:24,169
He looks like Gandalf the Gray!

7
00:00:24,169 --> 00:00:28,150
Today, I wanted to make a video with Best
Fiends because they are doing something

8
00:00:28,150 --> 00:00:31,890
really, really cool in honor of Earth Day.
They are running a charity campaign

9
00:00:31,890 --> 00:00:37,180
called Apps for Earth, they’ve teamed up with Apple and the World Wildlife Fund.

10
00:00:37,180 --> 00:00:40,440
For those of you who may not be familiar with
the World Wildlife Fund, they are a

11
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:44,469
charitable organization that helps to protect
the environment and all types of

12
00:00:44,469 --> 00:00:48,620
life on earth, like the Panda bear, that’s
their little logo, they have a little Panda!

13
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:50,060
He's super cute!

14
00:00:50,060 --> 00:00:54,379
It is a charitable organization that is near
and dear to my heart, so I wanted

15
00:00:54,379 --> 00:00:59,199
to get involved. For this campaign, Best Fiends
has put together 15 bonus levels

16
00:00:59,199 --> 00:01:03,250
which you get to play with cute little panda bear characters, aw!

17
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:07,730
From now until April 24th, if you purchase
a cute little panda bear character,

18
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:11,330
100% of the proceeds go to the World Wildlife
Fund.

19
00:01:11,330 --> 00:01:15,190
I got really excited about this and I wanted
to get behind it and get involved,

20
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:18,480
So, I got all of the pandas, I have got all
of them.

21
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,280
They’re adorable, I wanted to show you guys
what they look like.

22
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:28,070
There’s Lili, Bazoo, Scout, Leo and Daisy,
and they’re all friends!

23
00:01:28,070 --> 00:01:29,830
And you can play with them!

24
00:01:29,830 --> 00:01:32,670
Lili’s pretty cool too because she has these
two little purses on, and inside

25
00:01:32,670 --> 00:01:36,150
she's got a lot of cupcakes in there, so she’s
my kind of gal!

26
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,460
Beyoooooo! Get ‘em Scout!

27
00:01:39,460 --> 00:01:42,670
They’re teaming up with the bugs, to help
fight the slugs.

28
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:45,900
So in honor of the cute little panda bear
characters in the game

29
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:52,880
and the World Wildlife Fund, today we are
gonna be making some cute little DIY Panda Treats!

30
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,540
Let’s get started!

31
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:59,250
The first treat that we’re gonna be making
are these adorable Panda Macarons.

32
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:04,460
The things that you will need will be: 3/4
Cup of powdered sugar, 1/2 a cup and

33
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:10,679
2 tablespoons of almond flour, 2 egg whites,
1/4 cup of sugar and some black food

34
00:02:10,679 --> 00:02:15,060
coloring. And then for the filling, we will
need 1/2 a cup of heavy cream, 1 cup

35
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:20,120
of white chocolate chips. We will also need
a couple tips, I’ve got a #2A

36
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,709
and a #5 and some piping bags.

37
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:26,569
The first thing that we’re gonna do to make
our Panda Macarons, is, we’re going to

38
00:02:26,569 --> 00:02:31,109
sift together our powdered sugar and almond
flour. Here, I’ve got a bowl in the

39
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:34,519
middle, with a strainer, I’m gonna pour
both of these in here.

40
00:02:34,519 --> 00:02:35,230
And make it rain!

41
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:38,349
Make it rain, make it rain, make it rain,
make it rain!

42
00:02:38,349 --> 00:02:41,489
Now we’re gonna gently mix this up and set
it off to the side.

43
00:02:41,489 --> 00:02:44,739
Now we’re gonna make our meringue, the first
thing that you’re gonna do is

44
00:02:44,739 --> 00:02:47,780
you’re gonna crack 2 egg whites into this
bowl.

45
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:51,719
We’re first gonna mix together our
egg whites, until they’re frothy!

46
00:02:51,719 --> 00:02:55,790
This is what it looks like, kind of looks
like a bubble bath, it’s a bunch of bubbles.

47
00:02:55,790 --> 00:03:00,359
Now we’re going to slowly add our sugar,
just drizzle it really lightly,

48
00:03:00,359 --> 00:03:05,760
as we’re mixing, for about 3-4 minutes until
it forms stiff peaks!

49
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,340
Boom! We’ve got some peaks!

50
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:10,939
Now we’re gonna fold our dry ingredients
to our meringue.

51
00:03:10,939 --> 00:03:15,469
And remember, you want to fold it in, I like
to do it in thirds, just eyeballing it.

52
00:03:15,469 --> 00:03:20,909
And you cut it down the middle, and you fold
underneath and turn about halfway.

53
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:23,249
And keep doing this until it’s well incorporated.

54
00:03:23,249 --> 00:03:26,650
We’ve got it all mixed up and now i’m
just gonna take a little scoop.

55
00:03:26,650 --> 00:03:30,290
I’m just eyeballing it. We just need a little
bit to dye black.

56
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:34,760
I’m just gonna take a little bit of black
food coloring dye, add it to our batter.

57
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:37,019
Take a spoon, and mix it around.

58
00:03:37,019 --> 00:03:41,480
Our batter is now ready, I’ve placed it
over here into 2 plastic baggies, with

59
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,510
tips at the end for a little bit more control.

60
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:48,529
On the white batter I have the #2A tip, and
on the black batter I have the #5 tip.

61
00:03:48,529 --> 00:03:52,159
Over here I have a cookie sheet, lined with
a piece of parchment paper.

62
00:03:52,159 --> 00:03:56,999
On the bottom side, ooop! I’ve traced a
bunch of little circles, they’re about

63
00:03:56,999 --> 00:04:01,370
an inch and a half big, and then you want
to face them down.

64
00:04:01,370 --> 00:04:05,010
So that whatever side you draw on is on the bottom
and not touching the food.

65
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:09,700
We’re gonna take a little bit of batter
and just put a little dab into each corner,

66
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:10,700
and stick it down.

67
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:14,049
Now we’re gonna pipe our panda cookies,
we’re gonna start with the white batter.

68
00:04:14,049 --> 00:04:16,570
We’re just gonna fill in each circle.

69
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:20,230
We’ve got our cookies piped into the pan,
now we’re gonna give it a tap to get the

70
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,760
air bubbles out. This is loud, be careful!

71
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:28,260
Then you’re gonna take your black batter
and we’re gonna make the Panda’s ears

72
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:32,390
and facial features, but remember, we’re only
gonna be decorating half of them

73
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:35,670
with panda faces. Boop! Oh my gosh! So cute!

74
00:04:35,670 --> 00:04:39,790
Once you’ve got your Pandas piped, now we’re
gonna let them sit out at room

75
00:04:39,790 --> 00:04:44,720
temperature for about 30-40 minutes for them
to form a skin.

76
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:47,570
Once they’ve set, now we’re gonna bake,
you’re gonna heat your oven to

77
00:04:47,570 --> 00:04:53,310
325 degrees and bake these cookies for about
12-18 minutes.

78
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:59,030
And, look at this, nifty trick, we’re going
to double pan it while we bake,

79
00:04:59,030 --> 00:05:03,380
so that our macarons won’t burn at the bottom
and they will build taller feet!

80
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:06,340
While our cookies are baking, we’re gonna
be making out white chocolate ganache

81
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:10,920
filling. We’re gonna take our cream, a spatula,
our white chocolate chips, and

82
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:13,150
a pot, over to the stove!

83
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:18,380
To make our ganache filling, pour the cream
into the saucepan over medium-low heat.

84
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:22,030
Heat until it’s scalding, which is when
he teeny bubbles will start to form

85
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:24,160
all around the ring of the pan.

86
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:28,340
Then pour the warm cream over the white chocolate
chips and stir together

87
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:32,160
until smooth. Now we’re gonna place this
into the fridge to chill.

88
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:35,830
Our cookies have baked and I’ve given them
plenty of time to cool. And I just took

89
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:39,530
the ganache our of the fridge, put it into
a plastic baggie and I just cut

90
00:05:39,530 --> 00:05:41,770
the tip to make it a little bit easier. Now
we are gonna assemble.

91
00:05:41,770 --> 00:05:45,340
I’m just gonna pick up a bottom piece, put
a nice little layer of white

92
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:47,400
chocolate ganache, yum-yum-yum!

93
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:50,400
And then we’re gonna place on the top cookie.

94
00:05:50,410 --> 00:05:52,180
Oh my gosh, adorable!

95
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:54,030
Now we’re gonna do this to the rest of our
cookies!

96
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:58,920
And there you have it, here’s all of our
Panda Macarons that we made!

97
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:02,960
The next thing that we’re gonna be making
are Panda Panna Cottas!

98
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,160
Panda Cottas!

99
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,760
The things you will need to make the
Panna Cotta will be:

100
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:13,340
1 cup of milk, 1-1/2 cup of heavy cream, 1
cup of greek yogurt, 6 tablespoons

101
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:19,610
of water, 3/4 cup of sugar, 2 packets of powdered
gelatine, 1 teaspoon of vanilla

102
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:23,060
extract, and 1 teaspoon of almond extract.

103
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:28,810
You will also need some white candy melts,
black candy melts, and, a silicone mold!

104
00:06:28,810 --> 00:06:31,220
With these little 1/2 sphere cavities.

105
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:36,020
Then to make our brownies for the bottom,
you will need: 1 cup and 2 tablespoons

106
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:40,950
of sugar, 1/2 a cup of all purpose flour,
1/3 cup of dark cocoa powder,

107
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:47,220
1/3 cup of whole milk, 1/2 a cup of vegetable
oil, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon of vanilla

108
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:52,340
extract, 1/4 a teaspoon of salt, 1/4 a teaspoon
of baking powder, 3-1/4 inch

109
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:53,870
circle cookie cutter.

110
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:57,530
The first half of the treat is the panna cotta,
and that what we’re gonna make,

111
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:59,920
because it needs about 4 hours to set.

112
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:03,110
So, you’re gonna take your little bowl of
water and we’re gonna add

113
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:08,000
both the gelatine mixtures to the bowl. Take
your spoon, mix together.

114
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,520
Just put our gelatine off to the side, now
you’re gonna take your sugar,

115
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:15,000
cream, a whisk and pot over to the stove.

116
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,200
Add the cream into the saucepan and then the
sugar.

117
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:22,830
Whisk together until combined and then turn
the stove onto medium-low heat.

118
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:27,370
Continue whisking until the sugar is completely
dissolved and the cream is warmed.

119
00:07:27,370 --> 00:07:30,800
Then remove from the stove and back to your
baking station.

120
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:34,400
Just took our cream mixture off of the stove,
be careful because the outside of the

121
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:38,540
saucepan is hot, but our cream is very warm.
It’s interesting.

122
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:40,230
Just be careful, don’t get your fingers.

123
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:44,100
Now you’re gonna take your gelatin, add
it to your cream mixture, mix together

124
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:46,700
until the gelatine has fully melted.

125
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:50,040
Next we are gonna mix together some of our
wet ingredients, we are gonna mix

126
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:54,440
together our yogurt, our extracts, vanilla
and almond, and our milk into this

127
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:58,110
bowl right here. Then using a spatula, I’m
just gonna mix together.

128
00:07:58,110 --> 00:08:01,620
Here’s our cream mixture, we’re gonna
add it to the bowl now.

129
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:04,010
Whisk together one more time until fully combined.

130
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:08,330
I transferred our Panna Cotta mixture into a measuring
cup because it’s a little bit

131
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:11,620
easier to pour into the molds because it’s
got a spigot.

132
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:15,030
And, we’ve got our mold, I put it on top
of a baking sheet so it would

133
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:19,190
sit flat, it would be even. And, I’m
gonna give it a quick spray before

134
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:21,160
we pour in our Panna cotta Mixture.

135
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,510
It’s now time to fill up our molds.

136
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:26,120
You’re gonna fill them all the way to the
top!

137
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,440
Once your mold is filled, we’re gonna place
these in the fridge to set for

138
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:34,289
about 4 hours. While our Panna Cotta is chilling
in the fridge, we are gonna make

139
00:08:34,289 --> 00:08:38,430
some brownies for the bottom. Yum-yum-yum-yum-yum-yum-yum!

140
00:08:38,430 --> 00:08:41,370
The first thing that we’re gonna do is whisk
together some dry ingredients,

141
00:08:41,370 --> 00:08:46,399
in this mixing bowl right here. We are gonna
whisk together our flour, dark cocoa

142
00:08:46,399 --> 00:08:51,339
powder, sugar, baking powder, and salty-salty…

143
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,080
Dink!

144
00:08:54,449 --> 00:08:57,560
Then whisk together till everything’s
well combined.

145
00:08:57,560 --> 00:09:01,550
Next we’re gonna add our wet ingredients
to our dry ingredients, it doesn’t matter

146
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:04,209
what order, I love this recipe, it’s really
easy!

147
00:09:04,209 --> 00:09:11,629
We’re gonna add our oil, milk, vanilla,
and 1 full egg, and whisk together one

148
00:09:11,629 --> 00:09:14,100
more time, until everything is well combined.

149
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:17,399
Our brownie batter is ready, now we’re gonna
pour it into our pan.

150
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:22,069
Over here I’ve got our pan, it is 8x8 inch
square pan, which I’ve lined with

151
00:09:22,069 --> 00:09:25,249
a piece of parchment paper at the bottom.
And lightly sprayed it with

152
00:09:25,249 --> 00:09:29,560
baking spray because we’ll want to pop out
our brownies easily after they’ve baked.

153
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:33,339
And now, we’re gonna pour it in! Fill ‘er
up!

154
00:09:33,339 --> 00:09:36,600
Oh yum, you guys! This is like a chocolate
waterfall!

155
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:41,560
Our brownies are ready to bake, we’re gonna
heat our oven to 350 degrees and bake

156
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:45,259
for about 50 minutes. It’s a little bit
longer than normal, but it’s because we

157
00:09:45,259 --> 00:09:49,379
want our brownies to be pretty dry, to hold
the Panna Cotta on top!

158
00:09:49,379 --> 00:09:53,240
We took our brownies out of the oven, gave
it plenty of time to cool, I just popped

159
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:56,910
it out of the pan and placed it onto a cutting
board, I am now going to take the

160
00:09:56,910 --> 00:10:01,149
circle cookie cutter, and cut out the bottom
base of our Panna Cottas

161
00:10:01,149 --> 00:10:05,589
We cut out our brownies, our Panna Cottas
have set and now we’re gonna assemble

162
00:10:05,589 --> 00:10:08,000
our… Panda Cottas!

163
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,960
Ah! Hwah-hwah-hwah-hwah-hwah!

164
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:12,100
Alright, we’re just gonna pop these out,
I’m just gonna use my hands!

165
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:15,180
Ooooh! And, place it on top! Place it on top!

166
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:18,360
Now, time for my favorite part, it is time
to decorate!

167
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:22,100
I’ve got some candy melts that are black
that have not been melted. We’re gonna

168
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:26,009
use these for the ears. And then over here,
in these 2 little plastic baggies,

169
00:10:26,009 --> 00:10:30,800
I have some black melted candy melts, and
white melted candy melt.

170
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,129
You only need a little bit, you really don’t
need a lot!

171
00:10:33,129 --> 00:10:36,759
First thing I’m gonna do is place their
little ears, so you’re just gonna stick

172
00:10:36,759 --> 00:10:42,759
2 in at the top. And now, I’m just gonna
eyeball it, and draw 2 eyes, and a nose!

173
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:47,540
Da-dew! Here are all of the Panda Cotta Treats
that we made!

174
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:52,290
The next thing that we’re gonna be making
are these yummy little Panda Pudding Cups!

175
00:10:52,290 --> 00:10:57,309
The things you will need for the Panda Pudding
Cups will be: Some Oreos,

176
00:10:57,309 --> 00:11:01,649
4 dessert glasses, then for the pudding you
will need 2 cups of whole milk,

177
00:11:01,649 --> 00:11:07,309
1/3 cup of sugar, 3 tablespoons of corn starch,
2 pinches of salt, 2 tablespoons

178
00:11:07,309 --> 00:11:10,079
of butter, and 1/2 a vanilla bean.

179
00:11:10,079 --> 00:11:13,800
Then for the whipped cream you will need 1
cup of heavy whipping cream,

180
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:18,569
and, 2 tablespoons of sugar. You’ll also
need some black candy melts, and a

181
00:11:18,569 --> 00:11:20,670
1 ounce ice cream scoop.

182
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:24,550
The first thing that we’re gonna do, is we’re
gonna add our sugar, corn starch,

183
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:29,689
2 pinches of salt, and then I’m gonna whisk
together. Now I’m gonna slowly pour

184
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:33,009
the milk into the saucepan while whisking.

185
00:11:33,009 --> 00:11:34,509
High pour! High pour!

186
00:11:35,389 --> 00:11:39,959
After you’ve whisked everything together,
now we’re gonna add our vanilla bean!

187
00:11:39,959 --> 00:11:43,749
Over here I’ve slit the vanilla bean down
the middle, the long way.

188
00:11:43,749 --> 00:11:48,139
I’m gonna take a sharp cutting knife, and
scrape down to get all of the

189
00:11:48,139 --> 00:11:51,629
vanilla beans out. We’re gonna put all of
these little beans over here

190
00:11:51,629 --> 00:11:55,829
in our saucepan. Now we’re gonna take our
saucepan and head over to the stove!

191
00:11:55,829 --> 00:11:59,930
Turn your heat to medium-low, leave the mixture
on the stove until it’s nice

192
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:03,839
and warm and begins to thicken. Making sure
not to burn.

193
00:12:03,839 --> 00:12:08,329
Once it’s ready, remove from the stove and
take it back to your baking station.

194
00:12:08,329 --> 00:12:12,100
I just took the pudding off the stove, be
careful, it’s really, really hot.

195
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:16,300
Now I’m gonna pour it through our strainer.
I’ve got a bowl here, strainer

196
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:19,379
on the top. Remember, it’s hot, just be
careful, watch your fingers!

197
00:12:19,379 --> 00:12:21,539
And, we’re gonna add our butter.

198
00:12:21,540 --> 00:12:26,759
Using the spatula, I’m gonna mix in the
butter until it’s completely melted and shiny.

199
00:12:26,759 --> 00:12:31,709
I’m gonna let my pudding sit out at room
temperature for about 15-20 minutes,

200
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:35,029
and then I’m gonna cover the top with a
piece of plastic wrap, so that the

201
00:12:35,029 --> 00:12:38,429
pudding won’t form a skin, and pop it in
the fridge to chill.

202
00:12:38,429 --> 00:12:42,360
While our pudding is in the fridge, we are
gonna whip together our heavy whipping

203
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:45,619
cream and sugar, in this bowl right here.

204
00:12:45,619 --> 00:12:50,079
Then using a hand mixer, I’m gonna mix together
on a lower speed, until it becomes

205
00:12:50,079 --> 00:12:53,740
thicker, and then I’m gonna crank it up!
I’m gonna crank this up probably

206
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:54,649
to a 5!

207
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:57,550
Yum! Whipped cream, I’ll have a little bite!

208
00:12:57,550 --> 00:13:01,899
I’ve let the pudding set, in the fridge
to chill for 2 hours and now we are ready

209
00:13:01,899 --> 00:13:04,430
to assemble our cute little panda pudding
cups!

210
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:08,089
I’ve got my little cups laid out here, and
I’ve got the pudding, I’ve put it into

211
00:13:08,089 --> 00:13:11,720
a plastic baggie, and cut off the end for
just a little bit more control.

212
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:15,290
And then over here in this bowl, I’ve just
crushed up some Oreos, you can throw

213
00:13:15,290 --> 00:13:18,610
them in a blender, they’re all crushed up,
I left the filling in there.

214
00:13:18,610 --> 00:13:20,619
And we’re just gonna start stacking.

215
00:13:20,619 --> 00:13:24,980
It’s gonna go Oreos, pudding, Oreos, pudding.
We’re gonna layer it!

216
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:27,879
Time for my favorite part! It is time to decorate!

217
00:13:27,879 --> 00:13:30,790
Take your little ice cream scoop, we’re
gonna go over here to our whipped cream,

218
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:33,649
take a scoop, and we’re really gonna pack
it in there.

219
00:13:33,649 --> 00:13:37,329
And then, I’ve got a little hand towel over
here, and I’m just gonna tap it

220
00:13:37,329 --> 00:13:39,409
onto the side of the counter, like this.

221
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,620
It’s a little bit messy, but it’s really
gonna give it a nice shape.

222
00:13:43,629 --> 00:13:44,350
Here we go!

223
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:46,780
First one, we’re gonna flip it upside down,
oooop!!

224
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:50,339
We’re gonna pipe on simple panda faces using
our candy melts!

225
00:13:50,339 --> 00:13:55,720
2 little ears, little nose, and 2 eyes.

226
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:59,309
Now we’re gonna do this to make the rest
of our Panda Pudding Cups!

227
00:13:59,309 --> 00:14:00,629
Ta-da!

228
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:04,380
Here are all the DIY Panda Themed Treats that
we made today!

229
00:14:04,389 --> 00:14:12,199
We made, Panda Macaron Cookies, and, Panda
Cotta treats, and, last but not least,

230
00:14:12,199 --> 00:14:13,600
Panda Pudding Cups!

231
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:18,639
I’ll be posting lots of pictures of these
treats on Facebook, Tumblr, Instagram,

232
00:14:18,639 --> 00:14:22,089
and Twitter, and if you guys make any of these
Panda Themed treats, please take a

233
00:14:22,089 --> 00:14:25,279
picture and send it to me, I love seeing your
baking creations,

234
00:14:25,279 --> 00:14:27,720
it just makes my day, it makes me happy!

235
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:31,860
Special thanks to Best Fiends for sponsoring
and collaborating with me on this

236
00:14:31,860 --> 00:14:36,790
video, I just think it’s awesome that Best
Fiends, Apple, and World Wildlife

237
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:38,939
Fund teamed up to do something awesome.

238
00:14:38,939 --> 00:14:42,869
And, if you want to play Best Fiends, I’ll
put a link down below where you can try

239
00:14:42,869 --> 00:14:44,499
it and download it for free!

240
00:14:44,499 --> 00:14:47,259
Alright hope you guys like the treats, bye-bye!

I have been reading a sci-fi series, it’s

title: NINJA WEAPONS VS SODA!!
description:
WE EXPLODED SODA WITH AWESOME NINJA WEAPONS! CHECK OUT THIS AWESOME VLOG! Thanks to Best Fiends for sponsoring! Download the game for FREE here: http://download.BestFiends.com/BiggestEver 

Today Stephen Sharer, his brother Carter Sharer, and Lizzy Sharer went to visit their close friend Chad Wild Clay in California. Chad and Vy greeted the Sharers when they arrived. Chad then showed the Sharer around the house and even showed them his huge collection of Ninja weapons. Stephen, Carter, and Liz all picked an epic Ninja weapon and went outside. First Chad set up a water balloon and attacked it with nunchucks. The water balloon exploded blue water everywhere it was so cool. Next Liz used the crescent moon Ninja sword against a pumpkin. She swung the Ninja sword and easily sliced the pumpkin in half. Then Stephen was up next with his giant Nina sword. This sword is giant, and is about 6ft long. He swung the huge sword at a pumpkin and sliced into it half way. Then Carter was up next with his rainbow colored Ninja sword vs soda. Carter got into position and on the count of three he attacked the soda bottle. He stabbed the soda bottle and when the sword pierced the bottle it exploded fruit punch everywhere. Vy then finished up the Ninja weapons with an epic Halo energy sword vs a mini hydro dipped pumpkin. She easily sliced the pumpkin in half. Todays vlog was super fun and it was awesome to hang out with Chad Wild Clay and Vy. Comment #Ninja and what Ninja weapon was your favorite.

description:
Best Fiends was kind enough to sponsor this video! Click here to download Best Fiends for free: ​http://download.bestfiends.com | Click for the free template PDF, materials, and more info below ⬇

More of my DIY tutorials - http://bit.ly/DIYTutorialsPlaylist

Subscribe so you don’t miss a video! - http://bit.ly/LaurenFairweatherSubscribe

Download and print out the pattern PDF at http://www.laurenfairweather.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/mushroompincushiontemplate.pdf

Materials you'll need and links to where you can find them! Some of these are affiliate links, which means that I'd receive a small commission if you buy anything using them, at no extra cost to you! This helps me to keep making the videos you love. 
- Scissors - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3ik2/
- Colorful Cardstock (for the pins!) - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3m3t/
- Glue - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3m3q/
- White and purple felt - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3m3s/
- A small piece of thin cardboard. I used some empty packaging.
- Fabric Shears - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3hsl/
- Sewing needles - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3hsm/
- Thread - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3hsq/
- Sewing pins - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3ijw/
- Polyester Fiberfill - http://go.magik.ly/ml/3ikc/
- A small piece of tape
- Pennies or other small items to use as weights.

Here's a more detailed sewing tutorial for whipstitch in case you're new to hand sewing or need a refresher: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3lTAiUY69K8

title: Storybooth Daphne Revealed (Easter Egg)
description:
Subscribe: http://bit.ly/sub2storybooth | Thanks to Best Fiends for sponsoring! Download the game for FREE here: http://bit.ly/BestFiends-SB | Comment, like, share this story. Record your story at http://storybooth.com. 

Do you all know who Daphne is? If you've been watching storybooth videos for a little while then chances are you do, or at least you've seen her before. 

Daphne is a young animated actress, with dreams of fame and fortune, and she seems to have made storybooth her platform of choice. She way more than an Easter Egg. She's a social media and youtube Diva. She the Queen of the cameo. The Queen of photobomb. a wannabe youtuber. 

At first it was fine. She auditioned for Ainura K's video, "Caught Cheating in School," and we gave her a decent part - she was Ainura's best friend! But then Daphne kept showing up for auditions, and when she didn't get a part - well - she was obviously mad about it, but there was a certain devilish quality about her. She's very confident. She's also super persistent - relentless actually.

We're not quite sure when it started, and we're not even quite sure how she does it, but Daphne started showing up in episodes where she wasn't given a part. Sometimes in bizarre places.

We knew she was sneaky and not at all afraid to make trouble and try for the spotlight, but we had no idea she would go to such lengths to place herself conveniently into every episode. Let's face it, cameos and photobombs are her thing.  She calls them each a "guest appearance"...Hilarious! 

When we try to talk to her about it she just shrugs and assures us that one day she'll be famous and then storybooth will be happy to have had so much of her. 

She claims she brings us, and our subscribers and fans good luck. We think that might actually be true - we've had it so far - so we're a little scared to force her out. So you see, she far more that a storybooth Easter Egg. 

Besides, that's just Daphne being Daphne - an unstoppable force!

Can you name all the episodes in this video in the order they show up? Comment them if you can! 

This is a lot of Daphne, but not all of her - the harder to spot the greater the luck, so - good luck!

Thanks to our sponsor of this video Best Fiends. check them out at http://download.BestFiends.com/Biggest.  See the gameplay and a walkthrough here. 

What's your story?  storybooth wants to hear it!

What is ROBLOX? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 8 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet­to­be­dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“ROBUX”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms. 

► Check out Roblox: http://www.roblox.com/

If you'd like to see more Roblox videos like Life in Paradise, Escape the Evil Obby, or even crazy adventures like having a baby in Roblox, or stopping online dating in Roblox, be sure to click subscribe! :D

title: How to Make a 3D Frog Cake from Cookies, Cupcakes and Cardio
description:
Today I’m showing you how to make a 3D Frog Cake, modeled after the character Newt from Best Fiends. 
Click here to download Best Fiends for FREE: http://download.BestFiends.com/AprilPromo
This video was sponsored by Best Fiends! 

Blog post for this cake: http://cookiescupcakesandcardio.com/?p=9461

**********************
Subscribe to my NEW SECOND CHANNEL: https://goo.gl/gIoRUy
Visit my blog at:  http://cookiescupcakesandcardio.com
Subscribe: http://goo.gl/tuamEz
**********************

How to Make a 3D Frog Cake 

Ingredients:
3 Prepared 8” Vanilla Cake layers colored with 
-Layer 1 (5 drops green, 9 drops yellow),
-Layer 3 (2 drops green, 18 drops yellow),
-Layer 4 (2 drops green, 18 drops yellow, 10 drops white)
1 Prepared 9” Vanilla Cake layer (Layer 2) colored with 12 drops green, 9 drops yellow
Prepared vanilla buttercream 
Lime green, white, black, blue, yellow fondant 

Procedure:
1. Roll out white fondant for the eyes and mix with tylose to help harden them faster. Add blue and black for the iris and pupil. Shape the legs (216g) and the arms (91g) with lime green fondant (mixed with tylose). 
2. Prepare cakes according to the recipe, and color the batter according to the drop amounts listed above. 
3. Once cakes have cooled completely, place the darkest one on a cake board, attaching with a swipe of buttercream. Cover that layer with a thin layer of vanilla buttercream. Place the 9” cake on next, cover with buttercream, then the next darkest 8” cake. Finish the stack of cakes, with the lightest green one.
4. To begin carving the cake, start at the top, and gradually shape the cake to be at it’s widest at the 9” cake level, tapered under the 9” level, and then rising up to be smallest at the top. Reserve some of the cake scraps to make cake pop mixture for the vocal sac. 
Attach the vocal sac to the front of the cake. Cover the cake entirely in vanilla buttercream. 
5. Place a ring of fondant around the top of the cake, above the vocal sac. 
6. Roll out fondant, ⅛” in thickness and drape over the cake. 7. Smooth the fondant into place with your hands and a fondant smoother. 
8. Attach the arms, legs and eyes using skewers or spaghetti noodle. 
9. Serve the cake when desired and consume within 2-3 days.

PLAY FARM HEROES SUPER SAGA:  http://to.king.com/rosanna

Today I made Farm Heroes Super Saga Cropsie Cookies! Let me know down below what other videos you would like to see!

ORDER MY BAKING LINE: http://bit.ly/BakingLine
*Order The Nerdy Nummies Cookbook here: http://www.NerdyNummiesCookbook.com

CONNECT WITH RO:
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/rosannapansino
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/RosannaPansino
Tumblr: http://www.rosannapansino.tumblr.com
Instagram: http://instagram.com/rosannapansino
Snapchat: rosannapansino

FOLLOW NERDY NUMMIES HERE:
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/NerdyNummies/
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/NerdyNummies/
Twitter: http://twitter.com/nerdynummies

THE THINGS YOU WILL NEED: 
* (3) Cups All Purpose Flour: http://amzn.to/29kxiG1
* (3/4) Cup Almond Meal: http://amzn.to/29i7Ldt
* (1-1/2) Cups Sugar: http://amzn.to/29nuAzG
* (2) Sticks Salted Butter
* (1/8) Teaspoon Salt: http://amzn.to/29xdCRW
* (1) Teaspoon Baking Powder: http://amzn.to/29otD90
* (1/2) Teaspoon Ground Nutmeg: http://amzn.to/29uM9yG
* (1/2) Teaspoon Almond Extract: http://amzn.to/29uLZaf
* (1-1/2) Teaspoon Vanilla Extract: http://amzn.to/29uLOMk
* (2) Eggs

HELPFUL LINKS
* Water Drop Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29i8n2E
* Plum Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29nv3S9
* Banana Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29P8dSl
* Pear Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29r2ALV
* Carrot Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29xe2ri
* Tomato Cookie Cutter: http://amzn.to/29uMAsy

BIG THANK YOU
Monstercat Media for the song "Pump It"
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6R9FfC0Sen8
Song by: https://www.youtube.com/user/RezonateMusic
captions:
1
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:08,320
Hey guys it’s Ro! Welcome to another Nerdy
Nummies!

2
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:12,969
I have been playing a lot of app games lately
and you guys know me, I love games

3
00:00:12,969 --> 00:00:18,420
with food in them. And, I’ve fallen in love
with one recently called Farm Heroes.

4
00:00:18,420 --> 00:00:21,339
They just came out with their new game Farm
Heroes Super Saga,

5
00:00:21,339 --> 00:00:25,300
I really enjoyed playing this game and worked
with King Games who supported

6
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:28,560
this video to make some treats today. For those
of you who might not be

7
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:32,290
familiar with Farm Heroes, it’s a farming
themed match game, it’s very fun

8
00:00:32,290 --> 00:00:35,630
and easy to play. You need to match 3 Cropsies
to collect them and put them

9
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:40,130
in your crate. And, if you get 4 Cropsies
in a 4 square, they become

10
00:00:40,130 --> 00:00:43,190
Super Cropsies, and in this case bigger is
better!

11
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:45,000
You can also get more points this way.

12
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:49,420
So in honor of the new game, today we are
gonna be making Cropsie Themed Cookies.

13
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:50,870
Let’s get started!

14
00:00:50,870 --> 00:00:55,210
The recipe that we’re gonna be making today
is a vanilla almond homemade cookie

15
00:00:55,210 --> 00:00:57,010
recipe, this one is from the Nerdy Nummies
Cookbook.

16
00:00:57,010 --> 00:01:02,160
The things you will need, will be: 3 Cups
of all purpose flour, 3/4 cup of

17
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:07,260
almond meal, 1-1/2 cups of sugar, 2 sticks
of salted butter at room temperature,

18
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:12,440
1/8 a teaspoon of salt, 1 teaspoon of baking
powder, 1/2 a teaspoon of ground

19
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:17,600
nutmeg, 1/2 a teaspoon of almond extract,
1-1/2 teaspoons of vanilla extract,

20
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:22,750
and 2 eggs. Then you will also need some different
cookie cutters for the

21
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:26,930
Cropsie Characters. In the game they are so
cute! Over here I’ve got a water

22
00:01:26,930 --> 00:01:31,650
drop cookie cutter, a plum, banana, pear,
carrot… I think this one was

23
00:01:31,650 --> 00:01:35,180
technically a strawberry, but it looks just
fine as a carrot!

24
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:39,190
And, a little tomato. Now let’s put it all
together!

25
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:42,530
The first thing that we’re gonna do in a
medium bowl, we are gonna whisk

26
00:01:42,530 --> 00:01:47,510
together our dry ingredients, flour, almond
meal, salty-salty, baking powder

27
00:01:47,510 --> 00:01:51,729
and nutmeg. Then whisk together until well
combined and then we’re gonna set

28
00:01:51,729 --> 00:01:53,010
it off to the side.

29
00:01:53,010 --> 00:01:57,920
Next, in a large mixing bowl we are gonna
cream together our butter and sugar.

30
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:01,190
We are gonna mix together until everything
is light and fluffy.

31
00:02:01,190 --> 00:02:03,660
Now we are gonna mix in our eggs 1 at a time.

32
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:08,360
Add your first egg, mix it up, then scrape
down the sides, add your second

33
00:02:08,369 --> 00:02:10,989
egg, mix it up, and scrape down the sides.

34
00:02:10,989 --> 00:02:14,340
After we have mixed in our eggs we are going
to add both of our extracts,

35
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:18,280
vanilla and almond, then mix together until
well combined.

36
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:22,260
Everything is mixed together and now we are
gonna add our dry ingredients

37
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:26,370
to our butter mixture, I’m gonna be adding
it 1/2 at a time so that it

38
00:02:26,370 --> 00:02:30,269
won’t create a big dust cloud. Mix together,
then scrape down the sides

39
00:02:30,269 --> 00:02:34,180
then pour the other 1/2 in, mix together and
scrape down the sides.

40
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:39,239
Mmmmm! Our cookie dough is now ready, I’ve
divided it into 2 parts, we are

41
00:02:39,239 --> 00:02:44,260
gonna shape the dough into 2 discs and wrap
them up with food safe plastic wrap

42
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:47,409
and then pop these in the fridge for about
1 hour to chill.

43
00:02:47,409 --> 00:02:52,240
Our dough is ready, it has chilled in the
fridge, and now we are gonna roll it out.

44
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:55,419
And I’ve got it right here, we’ve gotta
unwrap it and I’m gonna do a little bit

45
00:02:55,419 --> 00:02:57,609
of what I call baking flair.

46
00:02:57,609 --> 00:02:59,999
Just grab it like this, and give it a tug!

47
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:05,599
We’re gonna take a little pinch of flour,
sprinkle it down on top of the surface

48
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:09,189
so that the dough won’t stick. Put a little
flour on top, a little flour

49
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:13,219
on my rolling pin. And then I’m gonna roll
it out about 1/4 inch thick.

50
00:03:13,219 --> 00:03:16,639
Alright, this is looking good, I’ve got
all the cookie cutters over here,

51
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:20,279
and we’re gonna cut out as many as you can.
I’m gonna start with the little plum.

52
00:03:20,279 --> 00:03:23,969
I’m gonna place it right here on top of
a baking sheet lined with a piece

53
00:03:23,969 --> 00:03:29,169
of parchment paper. Then I’ll do a little
carrot, a tomato. There’s plenty

54
00:03:29,169 --> 00:03:33,079
of cookie dough to make many of these little
Cropsies, but I’m just placing

55
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:37,329
6 Cropsies on each baking sheet so that they
have plenty of room.

56
00:03:37,329 --> 00:03:40,379
After you have your cookies on your baking
sheet you’re gonna pop these into

57
00:03:40,379 --> 00:03:44,010
the freezer for 10 minutes to set, and then
we’re gonna bake them.

58
00:03:44,010 --> 00:03:49,790
You’re gonna heat your oven to 350 degrees
and bake for about 12-13 minutes.

59
00:03:49,790 --> 00:03:53,569
Once your cookies have baked and had plenty
of time to cool, now it’s time

60
00:03:53,569 --> 00:03:56,879
to decorate. Over here I’ve got a bunch
of royal icing in different

61
00:03:56,879 --> 00:04:01,299
plastic baggies, with tips at the end for
a little bit more design control.

62
00:04:01,299 --> 00:04:07,129
The colors that I dyed the royal icing are
red, orange, yellow, green, blue,

63
00:04:07,129 --> 00:04:11,359
purple, white, light brown and this is very
dark brown.

64
00:04:11,359 --> 00:04:15,349
Over here on this cutting board, I’ve got
1 of each type of Cropsie Cookie.

65
00:04:15,349 --> 00:04:18,580
And the first thing that we’re gonna do
is pipe an outline.

66
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:21,340
So I’m gonna start with blue and we’re
gonna do the little water drop

67
00:04:21,340 --> 00:04:25,099
character. Just pipe an outline all the way
around.

68
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:29,530
Then we're gonna pipe outlines on each of our cookies
using the correct colors.

69
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:33,120
On some of the fruits and vegetables, I’m
not gonna pipe the stems.

70
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:36,520
Once your cookies are outlined, I’ve let
them sit out for just a few minutes,

71
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:40,919
so that the outline layer of royal icing hardens
a little bit, so it will

72
00:04:40,919 --> 00:04:44,960
hold shape. Now we’re gonna fill them in,
which in the baking world is

73
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:49,009
called flooding. I like to make zig-zags,
back and forth, back and forth

74
00:04:49,009 --> 00:04:53,240
and then using a toothpick, moving the icing
around so that it’s all touching,

75
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:56,930
all connecting. Then we’re gonna fill in
the rest of our cookies, continuing

76
00:04:56,930 --> 00:05:00,500
to match the colors. After you’ve filled
in all the cookies, again you’re gonna

77
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:04,199
want to let them set for a few minutes, I
like to take my finger and gently

78
00:05:04,199 --> 00:05:08,770
touch the top, and if I feel that it’s hardened
and dry, I know I can decorate

79
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:12,710
some more! Now I’m gonna take my white royal
icing, I’m gonna pipe all of their

80
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:16,900
little eyeballs. All of the eyeballs for the
different Cropsie characters are

81
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:21,750
different, so I’m just looking on my phone
and trying to match what they look like.

82
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:27,430
Time for more decoration details on the eyes.
We are gonna be piping iris’ and

83
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:29,310
the pupils on each little character.

84
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:34,080
It’s just good to note that their iris is
gonna be the same color as their body.

85
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:38,060
Lastly I’m just taking a little white royal
icing and I’m just putting a little

86
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:40,060
dot on each eyeball.

87
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:43,640
These are so cute, they’re really starting
to look like the Cropsies, look,

88
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:46,120
look at that little face! Aw!

89
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:50,639
But, they’re not done yet we have a few
more details. Again, using the dark brown,

90
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:55,560
I’m gonna pipe a line on top of each eyelid,
just giving it a little bit more

91
00:05:55,560 --> 00:06:00,500
personality and definition. And our little
plum gets some eyelashes!

92
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,720
Oooh-oooh-oooh!

93
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:06,580
These are starting to look adorable! We just
finished the eyes, now we are going

94
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:10,960
to decorate the mouth. All of our characters
are going to get a light brown

95
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:14,979
mouth, with a top line of dark brown for definition.

96
00:06:14,979 --> 00:06:18,580
And some of the characters will get a little
white royal icing, for their teeth!

97
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:22,770
Final decoration step is we are going to ice
the little stems on all the

98
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:27,860
Cropsies characters. Remember, the water does
not have a stem, and the pear is

99
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:30,360
the only one that we are gonna be icing brown.

100
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,960
But the rest of them are all green!

101
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,920
Ta-da! Here are the Cropsie Themed Cookies,
from the new game

102
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:39,759
Farm Heroes Super Saga, that we made today!

103
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:43,740
Each little Cropsie has it’s own personality,
the 2 that are my favorite, that

104
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:47,419
I think I’m the most like, are the pear
and the banana!

105
00:06:47,419 --> 00:06:51,699
The banana is excitable and a little bit crazy,
and the pear is sassy, feisty

106
00:06:51,699 --> 00:06:56,259
and kind. If you guys play the game, let me
know in the comments down below which

107
00:06:56,259 --> 00:07:00,909
little Cropsie personality you are most like.
Maybe you’re like the carrot,

108
00:07:00,909 --> 00:07:04,110
who’s confident, cheeky, ah-hee-hee-hee!
And happy!

109
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:07,439
I’ll be taking lots of pictures of these
cookies and posting them on Facebook,

110
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:10,490
Tumblr, Instagram and Twitter, and if you
guys make these, please take a

111
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:13,900
picture and send it to me, I just love seeing
your baking creations, it just

112
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,400
makes me happy, it makes my day.

113
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:19,469
A big thank you to King Games for supporting
and collaborating with me to

114
00:07:19,469 --> 00:07:23,180
make this video. If you guys are interested
in checking out this cute game

115
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:25,080
I’ll be putting a link down below.

116
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:30,280
And, if you have any other ideas for any other
Nerdy Nummies, please let me know,

117
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:33,409
leave me a comment down below and I will do
my best to make it happen!

118
00:07:33,409 --> 00:07:35,089
Alright, thanks again you guys, bye-bye!

Just as an update to upcoming videos: fandoms really fast is in the works! One more alt video after this one and then the next one will be going up 💕

title: The Philosophy of BOJACK HORSEMAN – Wisecrack Edition
description:
Watch Wisecrack's Quick Take on Bojack Horseman Season 4 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T_JSk1UZDbU
Join Wisecrack! Subscribe! ►►http://bit.ly/1y8Veir 

Welcome to this special Wisecrack Edition on The Philosophy of BoJack Horseman, exploring the dark existential undertones of this seemingly light-hearted cartoon. Behind the colorful animations and snarky one-liners is a show that's astonishingly deep – a series that ponders important philosophical questions about living life in a meaningless universe. From Pascal to Sartre, we'll dive into the thinkers and philosophies that are foundational to the show's underlying message.

title: Brooklyn & Bailey Cover Mother's Day | Behind the Braids Ep.3
description:
Come along to see what Mother's Day is like for Mindy in the CGH home, and click below to download Best Fiends for FREE! http://download.bestfiends.com

Happy Mother's Day to all of you moms and grandmothers out there! We are super appreciative to Best Fiends for partnering with us on this special vlog for you! This day is one of my most favorite days of the year! Why is that? Because Shaun and the kids do their "very best" to make sure it is a day where I don't have to worry about schedules, cooking, cleaning, refereeing, morning and nighttime routines, etc? No, it isn't even all of those things being taken care of. Yes, I love the hand drawn cards and the gifts that I get from them, too, yet it isn't all of those things that I enjoy the very most either! I sure enjoy all the personal time the kids give me, but it isn't that either. Well, then... what is it?

I love Mother's Day because I get to reflect on my own mother, and my grandmothers who have passed on, and what I love most about them all. Then I get to hug and hold each of my own children, cherishing the very best of motherhood. It's those giggles, hugs, kisses, and "I love you, mommy!" statements that I love the very most!

Please be sure to give this video a BIG "👍🏻" if you loved it, then please go give your own mom (or other influential female figure) a huge hug or a quick phone call to tell her how much she means to you. Then leave a comment below telling us that you have done that!

We hope that you all enjoy this Behind the Braids look into our home on Mother's Day, and feel a part of our family. We love each one of you!

💋's -Mindy
___

We post a new hairstyle tutorial or Behind the Braids family vlog every Sunday night.  Abby and Annie post a guest post hairstyle every Thursday night {7pm CST}! 

So, please don't forget to subscribe to our YouTube channel...
http://www.youtube.com/user/CuteGirlsHairstyles?sub_confirmation=1

Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/CuteGirlHair
Instagram: http://www.Instagram.com/CuteGirlsHairstyles
Pinterest: http://www.pinterest.com/MrsHairdo

About Cute Girls Hairstyles: 
Mindy McKnight is a mother of six children and a teacher of all braids, past, present, and future! Enjoy hundreds of 5-minute hairstyles that are cute and easy to recreate! Whether you're looking to learn how to create waterfall braids, french braids, fishtail braids, lace braids, pancake braids, faux braids, plaits, twists, buns, ponytails, updos or something with a little edge... you can find it all here! (We even have Daddy Do's, hairstyles so easy that even a daddy can do them!)  Be sure to subscribe... and prepare for compliments!

title: 15 DIY Halloween Costume Ideas for Best Friends or Couples | Brooklyn and Bailey
description:
Want to see 15 DIY Halloween Costumes that are perfect for couples, best friends, or your squad?? This is the perfect Halloween costume video for you! These are perfect last-minute DIY Halloween costumes for your Squad, BFF, or couples.  

Be sure to follow us on musical.ly @BrooklynAndBailey, and watch our funny music clips! http://www.musical.ly We are having so much fun on it!

This video definitely shows you awesome DIY Halloween costumes for girls, kids and teenagers as well as older Halloween lovers like parents, couples, and adults. First, we’ll show you our DIY Halloween Baseball Player costume, perfect for a last minute Halloween costume with stuff you likely already have! This DIY Halloween costume includes a baseball t-shirt, baseball hat, denim jeans, and some cute athletic socks. Pop in some bubble gum and you’re set! 
 
Next up, we show you our Peanut Butter & Jelly last-minute DIY Halloween Costume. How easy is this? We bought a brown shirt and a red shirt from Target and added some vinyl lettering to say “peanut butter” and “jelly”. 
 
What about a Pizza & Pizza Delivery Guy DIY Halloween Costume?  Bailey reused the same baseball tee and hat from our previous Baseball Player Costume and paired it with some ripped denim jeans, Converse, and a pizza box. Brooklyn wore an all black outfit with a DIY Halloween prop to look like a giant slice of pizza. Kamri tells you how to make the pizza slice in her video here: https://youtu.be/ybby956ynC8.
 
Next, we opted for a DIY Halloween Cop & Donut costume! We picked up the police outfit on Amazon and completed it with handcuffs. Bailey’s Halloween costume also uses a DIY Donut prop. Under the doughnut she wore an all white outfit to keep it clean and simple. She also opted for a simple hair bun Halloween hairstyle. Kamri also tells us how to make the donut in her video Here: https://youtu.be/ybby956ynC8.
 
We decided to do something for those people trick or treating on Halloween in threes… a DIY Halloween costume of the Three Blind Mice! We used matching black clothing from our closets and paired them with mouse ears, gloves, sunglasses, canes, and matching black bowties. Adding some fun Halloween makeup like bright red lipstick is a nice pop, too!
 
You may know of Elliot and Gertie, from the movie ET, who served as inspiration for our next costume! For Gertie’s DIY costume, you’ll need black overalls, striped shirt, sunflowers, & Reece’s Pieces. Cute pigtails with ribbons perfectly round out her costume. For Elliot, we use ripped jeans, red hoodie, and cute basket with an ET stuffed animal (wrapped up in blanket with his cute red heart showing thru). 
 
Our Google Maps Pin DIY Halloween costume is up next! Grab a grey t-shirt, add yellow duct tape, and printed street names and destinations.  We also cut out giant red poster board pins to wear on our faces. This couples costume is ADORABLE! 
 
The DIY Piñata & Birthday Boy is also a cute Halloween costume idea! We found birthday supply items from Walmart and wore them as decorations. We cut the edges of felt to create a piñata fringe look and then hot glued that all to a dress we bought. We also used two Styrofoam cones and added the fringe there as well to create a cheap and inexpensive DIY piñata headband.
 
Superheroes create a cute look and are definitely a last minute Halloween costume option since it only requires a couple superhero t-shirts, denim shorts, some cute socks and shoes, and a bow to match the shirts. Brooklyn opted for a Superman t-shirt and Bailey picked a Batman t-shirt for this last minute Halloween costume. 
 
This year Pokemon is all the rage, so why not create couples Halloween costumes of Pikachu & Ash Ketchum? We bought Pikachu ears and tail from Amazon and paired it with a yellow tee and socks. Bailey wore a cute Ash Ketchum baseball hat with a simple white tee and jeans!
 
Our DIY Scuba Diver costumes are our personal favorites! We created our DIY scuba gear out of 2 liter soda bottles, black tubing, pacifiers, and fun foam to create the belt. We added DIY flippers out of fun foam to fit over our shoes and some snorkeling masks and headed out to sea!

If you loved this video, please give it a HUGE "👍🏼", and comment below with which couples costumes you loved the most!

💜's -Bailey

_

Don't forget to subscribe to our YouTube channel...
http://www.youtube.com/user/BrooklynAndBailey?sub_confirmation=1

Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/BrooklynAndBailey
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/BrookAndBailey
Instagram: http://www.Instagram.com/BrooklynAndBailey
Follow us on SnapChat: @BrookAndBailey

_

FTC Disclaimer: This is not a sponsored video.
_

💥SUPERFANS💥: You can help us translate this Epic Slumber Party video, and get credit below! Click here: http://www.youtube.com/timedtext_video?ref=share&v=xgerx-qK7Cc

To help us translate other videos (and be our fav people ever!) click here: http://www.youtube.com/timedtext_cs_panel?tab=2&c=UC6QWhGQqf0YDYdRb0n6ojWw

title: Stephen Sharer - Share the Love (Official Music Video)
description:
Share the Love - Original Song by Stephen Sharer ft. Carter Sharer and Lizzy Sharer

🎶 GET THE TRACK 🎶
▶︎ ITUNES (https://goo.gl/fyqRES)
▶︎ SPOTIFY (https://goo.gl/ZGHjjw)

Today Stephen Sharer, Carter Sharer, and Liz decided to make the most epic music video vlog ever. Stephen and Carter ran outside to get things started. Stephen started by modding Nerf guns to make them stronger. Carter then stepped things up a notch and pulled out the Worlds Largest Nerf rocket launcher. Stephen then gave the Worlds Largest Fidget Spinner a huge spin. Then Carter climbed in the skid steer machine, Stephen jumped in the pool.  Carter dumped the huge bucket full of Orbeez and made a huge Orbeez waterfall all over Stephen. Then Carter hopped on his mountain bike and rode down the hill and hit the huge mega ramp and just like in the Roman Atwood Backflip Challenge, Carter did an epic backflip into the pond. Carter then rode on the Worlds biggest hoverboard and to top it off he did an epic wheelie on his dirt bike. Now it was Liz’s turn to make things epic.  Liz started off by running on water and across the pond. She then filled up a huge water balloon on the trampoline and climbed inside. Then Stephen and Carter bounced her and the huge water balloon on the trampoline. Then Carter popped the giant water balloon while Liz was flying through the air on the trampoline. Then Stephen, Carter, and Liz ran down to the pond and climbed on the floating water trampoline. All at once they jumped off and did a backflip into the water. To top it off the Sharer's all climbed in a lime green Lamborghini and drove off into the sunset. If you thought this was the most epic vlog ever then comment #MusicVideo and smash the like button. 

This music video and song captures the spirit of the Stephen Sharer channel and consolidates the positive message to help spread love around the world, Share the Love. 

😊 This channel is family-friendly and kid-friendly, so everyone can join in on the fun! Share The Love!! 😊🤘
