title: DIY Gift Ideas! 10 DIY Christmas Gifts & Birthday Gifts for Best Friends
description:
DIY Gifts! In this DIY gift ideas I show 10 DIY Christmas gifts, birthday gifts or gifts for any other occasion. DIY Christmas gifts for best friends, boyfriend, girlfriend and family are always better than store bought presents. DIY gifts are much more unique. The 10 DIY gift ideas are perfect for Christmas presents and birthday presents or you can make them for yourself. These 10 awesome DIY projects include DIY clothes, DIY room decor, DIY treats and more... A perfect holiday gift guide!

http://sarabeautycorner.com/

Take some time this year and make DIY Christmas gifts for best friends and family! The DIY gifts Ideas are perfect for best friends, girlfriend, boyfriend, mother, father, grandpa, grandma - you can really find something for everyone in this holiday gift guide. All 10 gift ideas are easy to make, perfect for beginners in crafts.
 
DIY gifts in a box are always adorable, if they are thematic – even better! I show you how to simply make a DIY ice cream sundae in a box. This is a perfect DIY gift idea for best friends, family or anyone that loves deserts. You can give it as a Christmas gift or a birthday gifts because we love ice cream all year around!
 
You can make a DIY sweater as a Christmas gift, birthday present for your best friends and family or for yourself. This DIY fashion piece is so easy and quick to make but turns out adorable – which to me is the most important when making DIY projects. This gift is also very affordable, since you can get a plain sweater for very cheap. If you are making the DIY project for yourself feel free to use your old sweater and give it a new life. DIY projects that include recycling clothes are always so much fun!
 
One of my favorite DIY gifts is a picture frame. Buy a cheap picture frame and decorate it yourself. You can color the frame and stick flowers or other decorations on it. Great DIY Christmas gift or a birthday present all year around. This is a pretty DIY room décor that you can make for yourself too.

Ear hats are a huge trend and can be such a cute Christmas gift! I show how you can make them yourself for very cheap. This is one of the cutest DIY projects I have ever tried. You guys know how I love DIY clothes projects. If I happen to give my hat away as a present, I will definitely recycle one of my old hats and make one for myself.
 
As cute little DIY inexpensive gifts you can make bonbons full of yummy candy. Using a paper roll and some wrapping paper you can package candy into adorable bonbons. Such a pretty gift idea for anyone you love. You can also use these as stocking fillers!
 
You don’t have to be a cooking expert to make delicious chocolate bonbons. All you need for this adorable gift idea is some chocolate, molds and sprinkles. You can also make healthy chocolates by topping them with dried fruits or chopped nuts. This gift idea is perfect for Christmas, birthdays, Valentine’s day or any kind of day when you want to surprise loved ones.

Beauty DIY gift ideas are perfect DIY presents for beauty enthusiasts! I show you how to make a moisturizing DIY scrub. I added some peppermint extract so this one really smells like Christmas. The main ingredients you need are coconut oil and sugar. I love using this DIY scrub myself. Especially in the winter when my skin gets dry this DIY scrub removes dead skin cells and moisturizes like a dream!
 
Room decorations are great as DIY gift ideas for any age. I show  how to make easy DIY clay bowls, which can be used as decorating and organizing pieces. You can use them to store  jewelry, keys, pins or other small bits and pieces. These DIY presents are also so much fun to make!
 
DIY mugs can be an awesome gift for Christmas, birthday, or any other occasion. You can be so creative with designs – write on some funny or inspiring quotes, draw pictures and just have fun creating these awesome DIY gifts.

My favorite of all these DIY gift ideas are probably DIY gloves. What I love the most is that you don’t have to know how to knit to make these awesome DIY mittens. All you need is yarn, bobby pins and an ice cream cup. These are such a thoughtful, unique and special DIY gift. Another awesome DIY fashion project. DIY gloves are perfect for girls, boys, father and mom. I promise that this diy will melt heart of anyone!

00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:02,070
and looking awesome. I love how you can be
so creative with these mugs. You can make

194
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:08,460
so many awesome designs. Drawings, patterns,
quotes... sky is the limit. Quality control

195
00:18:08,460 --> 00:18:13,730
is needed again so let's make some hot chocolate.
Little bit of milk, a teaspoon of cocoa powder

196
00:18:13,730 --> 00:18:18,350
and whipped cream to make it extra delicious
and festive. Every time your friend will drink

197
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:23,240
from the mug that you made, he or she will
be reminded how special he or she is to you.

198
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,230
And that is a priceless feeling.

199
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:31,820
Last but definitely not least I'll show you
how to make these epic gloves or hand warmers,

200
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:36,039
which is probably my favorite gift idea in
a bunch. And no worries if you don't know

201
00:18:36,039 --> 00:18:41,280
how to knit because I have no clue either,
tweenzies! You will need some yarn, ice cream

202
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:46,789
cup, glue gun, bobby pins, knitting hook and
a needle. Before we start knitting we need

203
00:18:46,789 --> 00:18:51,650
to make a simple knitting loom. Start placing
pairs of pins around the edge of the cup like

204
00:18:51,650 --> 00:18:56,220
that, leaving about half an inch between each
pair. If you don't have an ice cream cup you

205
00:18:56,220 --> 00:19:01,360
can use a bigger coffee cup or any other hollow
rounded object. Time to take our glue gun

206
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:05,549
and let's apply some glue over and around
each pin to make sure they will stay in place

207
00:19:05,549 --> 00:19:16,299
while knitting. When all the pins are glued
in place we can proceed to the fun part – knitting!

208
00:19:16,299 --> 00:19:21,140
Take your yarn and this is optional – a
straw. Thread the yarn through it. Straw makes

209
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:26,100
it easier to wrap the yarn around each pin.
Leave about five inches of yarn hang loose

210
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:30,330
and then start wrapping the yarn around each
pin. Make sure that you have loops on the

211
00:19:30,330 --> 00:19:36,410
outside and the connecting line of yarn on
the inside of the loom. When you reach the

212
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:41,030
first pin, just continue with one more row
above the first one. See how quickly you can

213
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:46,210
wrap the yarn around the pins using a straw?!
The second wrapping row is finished so it's

214
00:19:46,210 --> 00:19:50,919
time to take the hook and pull the bottom
loops over the top ones. Grab the bottom loop

215
00:19:50,919 --> 00:19:55,330
– the one closer to the cup edge – pull
it over the top loop and over the pin like

216
00:19:55,330 --> 00:20:00,020
that. If you don't have a hook you can easily
make one from a piece of wire or you can pull

217
00:20:00,020 --> 00:20:06,740
with fingers too. Go all around the loom until
our first row is finished. Time to again wrap

218
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:11,080
the around the pins – but from now
on we only need to wrap them once, because

219
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:16,960
as you can see, we already have our first
row of yarn from before. When all the pins

220
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:21,380
are wrapped take a hook and pull the bottom
loops over the top ones. These are the two

221
00:20:21,380 --> 00:20:26,130
steps that you need to keep repeating until
your glove is long enough: wrap the yarn around

222
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:30,460
the pins, pull the bottom loops over the top
ones. Then again wrap the yarn around the

223
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:34,980
pins and again pull the bottom loops over
the top ones, it's that simple! You can make

224
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:39,539
the gloves using only one color of yarn, or
you can make stripes of different colors.

225
00:20:39,539 --> 00:20:44,340
I decided to make a green edge on these gloves
so I need to switch the yarn. This is very

226
00:20:44,340 --> 00:20:50,140
easy. Snip the pink working yarn, leaving
about five inches extra like that. Take the

227
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:55,510
green yarn and thread on a straw. Now simply
make a knot tying together the pink and green

228
00:20:55,510 --> 00:21:01,140
yarn like that. Then continue the same two
easy steps as before. This time using green

229
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:05,840
yarn. Wrap the yarn around each pin and then
pull the bottom loops over the top ones. And

230
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:10,600
that's the whole story, it's really easy,
you really have to try. I love this quick

231
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:14,770
loom knitting technique because it is so simple
and it only takes about two hours to make

232
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:19,150
a beautiful glove! Especially this time of
the year, when it gets dark so quickly I love

233
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:24,190
cosying up on the couch wrapped in blankets,
watch some TV and knit these gloves. I find

234
00:21:24,190 --> 00:21:29,940
it really relaxing and therapeutic. Call me
granny, it's like "granny's beauty corner".

235
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:34,400
After twenty two pink and five green rows
I believe this glove is long enough so I am

236
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:38,309
going to pull the bottom loops over the top
ones for the last time and then we'll make

237
00:21:38,309 --> 00:21:45,179
a finishing crochet row. To make it you can
use a crochet hook like me, but the knitting

238
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:49,919
hook from before or a piece of wire would
work just fine too. Pull the first loop from

239
00:21:49,919 --> 00:21:55,200
the pin and onto the hook. Take your working
yarn and wrap it around the hook like this.

240
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:59,730
Now you need to pull the first loop over the
second one and off the hook. Add the loop

241
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:04,280
from the second pin onto the hook and again
wrap the working yarn around the hook. As

242
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:09,200
you can see you have three loops on the hook.
Pull the middle one over the third loop and

243
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:14,070
then the first one over the third loop. Continue
this step until you take all the loops off

244
00:22:14,070 --> 00:22:19,679
the pins. I feel like I'm saying "hook" hundred
billions times now, but I really want you

245
00:22:19,679 --> 00:22:26,450
guys to understand. Let's repeat: take the
loop of the pin, wrap the working yarn around

246
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:31,340
the hook and you're left with 3 loops on the
hook. Pull over the middle one and the first

247
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:37,169
one. Then repeat the step. When you reach
your last pin, the glove will come off the

248
00:22:37,169 --> 00:22:47,039
loom. You are left with a little loop and
the working yarn which we have to trim leaving

249
00:22:47,039 --> 00:22:51,780
about five inches of extra. Lead the yarn
through the loop and make a couple of knots

250
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:56,710
and stitches to make sure that the glove won't
fall apart. We want it to last many years.

251
00:22:56,710 --> 00:23:04,720
I am using a big knitting needle but you can
totally make one using a piece of wire. On

252
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:09,250
the opposite end of the glove you still have
this first yarn end peaking out. Make a few

253
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:17,809
knots and stitches to secure your work. I
decided to make an extra knot where we switched

254
00:23:17,809 --> 00:23:22,980
the colors just to be sure. Now we can snip
away all that extra yarn hanging out. Push

255
00:23:22,980 --> 00:23:26,970
the knot from the yarn switch inside the glove
to hide it and we are all done, and ready

256
00:23:26,970 --> 00:23:31,900
to admire these adorable hand knitted gloves.
You can make them for yourself or you can

257
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:36,289
give them as the most beautiful and thoughtful
gift ever. Switch up the colors and you can

258
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:41,460
make these gloves for anyone – girlfriend,
boyfriend, grandpa and I guarantee they will

259
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,460
be overwhelmed.

260
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:47,940
Home made gifts are much more thoughtful,
unique and special then the store bought ones.

261
00:23:47,940 --> 00:23:51,690
Take some time this year and make gifts for
your friends and family and show them how

262
00:23:51,690 --> 00:23:56,250
much they mean to you! You will melt their
heart, because with home made gifts you don't

263
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:58,289
give an object – you give love.

264
00:23:58,289 --> 00:24:03,429
These were my ten DIY gifts ideas perfect
for Christmas, birthdays or any kind of day

265
00:24:03,429 --> 00:24:06,610
when you want to tell your friends and family
that you love them. Let me know in the comments,

266
00:24:06,610 --> 00:24:10,590
which of the ten ideas was your favorite and
also give the video some love if you want

267
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:14,830
more Christmas related videos, maybe a room
decor or something like that. Let me know...

268
00:24:14,830 --> 00:24:18,570
That is it for today, thank you so much for
watching and I'll talk to you really soon.

269
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:22,279
Oh and before I go, don't forget to check
out the Christmas videos, I did last year.

270
00:24:22,279 --> 00:24:24,679
Bye! Please Subscribe

title: Making Some Changes! | Thomas Sanders
description:
Changes in our lives can be scary and disorienting at times, and I've been going through my fair share of them. I find my self longing for the simpler times with familiar faces, so the different aspects of my personality step in to convince me I shouldn't be afraid of change... or stick to what is familiar. Hope you enjoy it!! 

This video was co-written by me and my amazing friend, Joan!!

Thank you SO MUCH to my amazing friends who helped with this video!! Here are their links so you can see more of them!!

Joan: @welcome_to_the_joangle (Instagram); @welcome-to-the-joangle (Tumblr)
Talyn: @tallykat3 (Instagram, Tumblr, and Twitter)

James takes over the mic and camera for this episode to share his own personal experiences with game compulsion--and most importantly, how he overcame it and went on to start his career in the game industry, and have a fulfilling life in general.

lift me from this hole?  Be my
hands forever stained
with a thousand smears
from the blood and tears!

title: HOW TO MAKE WARCRAFT COOKIES - NERDY NUMMIES
description:
Today I made Warcraft Horde and Alliance Faction Logo Cookies in celebration of the Warcraft movie coming out! I really enjoy making nerdy themed goodies and decorating them. I'm not a pro, but I love baking as a hobby. Please let me know what kind of treat you would like me to make next. 

ORDER MY BAKING LINE: http://bit.ly/BakingLine
*Order the Nerdy Nummies Cookbook here: http://www.nerdynummiescookbook.com

FOLLOW ME HERE:
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/rosannapansino
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/RosannaPansino
Tumblr: http://www.rosannapansino.tumblr.com
Instagram: http://instagram.com/rosannapansino
Snapchat: rosannapansino

FOLLOW NERDY NUMMIES HERE:
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/NerdyNummies/
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/NerdyNummies/
Twitter: http://twitter.com/nerdynummies

LOGO TEMPLATES:
Horde Logo: http://tinyurl.com/HordeTemplate
Alliance Template: http://tinyurl.com/AllianceTemplate

THE THINGS YOU WILL NEED: 
* (3) Cups All Purpose Flour: http://amzn.to/24wmZkx
* (2) Sticks Butter
* (1-1/2) Cups Sugar: http://amzn.to/1TXyrpI
* (1) Teaspoon Baking Powder: http://amzn.to/25JXxdT
* (1/8) Teaspoon Salt: http://amzn.to/28hQNGh
* (1) Teaspoon Vanilla Extract: http://amzn.to/24wnmfa
* (2) Eggs
* (1) Bag Black Royal Icing
* (1) Bag Blue Royal Icing
* (1) Bag Yellow Royal Icing
* (1) Bag Red Royal Icing

BIG THANK YOU
Monstercat Media for the song "Pump It"
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6R9FfC0Sen8
https://www.youtube.com/user/RezonateMusic

This is not a sponsored video. All products purchased by me.
captions:
1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,160
Hey guys, it’s Ro! Welcome to another Nerdy
Nummies!

2
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:12,019
I got so many requests to make something Warcraft
themed, the Warcraft movie just came

3
00:00:12,019 --> 00:00:15,999
out and I have a lot of friends who play Warcraft
and World of Warcraft.

4
00:00:15,999 --> 00:00:19,939
I am a huge fan of Blizzard games and I am
dressed up as a Gnome!

5
00:00:19,940 --> 00:00:23,700
Which are my favorite playable characters.
They are very petite, they’re tinkerers

6
00:00:23,710 --> 00:00:26,099
and they’ve got a Steampunk style!

7
00:00:26,099 --> 00:00:30,320
I feel like if I was a Warcraft character
in real life I would be a Gnome!

8
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:35,040
Today we are gonna be making traditional Warcraft
Horde and Alliance themed cookies!

9
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:36,800
Let’s get started!

10
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:42,300
The things you will need, will be: 3 cups
of all purpose flour, 2 sticks of butter,

11
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:47,030
1-1/2 cups of sugar, 1 teaspoon of baking
powder, 1/8 teaspoon of salt,

12
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:52,720
1 teaspoon of vanilla, and 2 eggs. Then you will
also need 4 different colors of royal

13
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:58,920
icing, I’ve dyed them black, blue, yellow
and red. And a circle cookie cutter.

14
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:01,220
Now let’s put it all together!

15
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:05,580
The recipe that we’re using today is an
adaptation from my lemon sugar cookie recipe

16
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:08,960
from the Nerdy Nummies Cookbook. The first
thing that we’re gonna do is we’re gonna

17
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:14,530
combine our dry ingredients into this bowl.
We’re gonna add our flour, salt and

18
00:01:14,530 --> 00:01:18,000
baking powder. Then we’re gonna whisk it
together until it’s well combined.

19
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:22,320
Next we’re gonna cream together our butter
and sugar into a big mixing bowl.

20
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:25,500
So I’m gonna put in my butter, add your
sugar, now I’m gonna mix together

21
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:29,360
until our mixture is light and fluffy. I’m
using my Wiz-o-Matic 5000!

22
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:32,680
Or you can use a hand mixer, whatever you
got!

23
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:35,600
It’s light and fluffy, now we’re gonna
add our eggs.

24
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:40,580
We’re gonna add them 1 at a time, add the
egg, mix it up, scrape down,

25
00:01:40,580 --> 00:01:44,270
then add your second egg, mix it up and scrape
down again.

26
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:48,570
Then add your vanilla extract and mix it up
1 more time!

27
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:52,760
Our wet ingredients are all mixed up and now
we are gonna pour in all

28
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:56,729
of our dry ingredients. And now we’re gonna
mix it together, but you want to make

29
00:01:56,729 --> 00:02:00,240
sure it’s on a low speed, otherwise you’ll
get a big dust cloud!

30
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:03,659
Our cookie dough is mixed and it’s ready
to chill, we’re gonna wrap it up in

31
00:02:03,659 --> 00:02:08,489
plastic wrap. Now I’m gonna put this into
the fridge and let it chill for about 2 hours.

32
00:02:08,489 --> 00:02:12,639
Our dough has sat in the fridge, it’s chilled,
and now it’s ready to roll out.

33
00:02:12,639 --> 00:02:16,579
We’re gonna unwrap our dough…. Yes!

34
00:02:16,580 --> 00:02:20,000
We’re gonna take a little bit of flour,
sprinkle it on top of our work surface

35
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:23,529
so that the dough doesn’t stick. And I’m
going to be cutting my dough in 1/2

36
00:02:23,529 --> 00:02:27,060
and rolling it out 1/2 at a time so it’s
a little bit easier to work with!

37
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:31,340
Sprinkle a little flour on top, and on your
rolling pin, and get to rolling!

38
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:34,260
We’re gonna roll it out about 1/4 inch thick.

39
00:02:34,269 --> 00:02:38,340
Now we’re gonna cut out our cookies, take
your circle cookie cutter, and cut out

40
00:02:38,340 --> 00:02:42,950
as many as you can. Remove your excess dough.
I’m gonna place these on a baking

41
00:02:42,950 --> 00:02:47,279
sheet lined with parchment paper, this recipe
doesn’t spread very much, it

42
00:02:47,279 --> 00:02:50,319
really holds shape, so you can put these cookies
pretty close.

43
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:53,269
Once you’ve got your cookies on the tray,
we are gonna bake them, you’re gonna heat

44
00:02:53,269 --> 00:02:58,090
your oven to 350 degrees and bake for about
12-14 minutes.

45
00:02:58,090 --> 00:03:01,269
While the oven is pre-heating, this part is
totally optional, but I’m gonna pop

46
00:03:01,269 --> 00:03:04,869
these cookies in the freezer to help hold
their shape while they bake.

47
00:03:04,869 --> 00:03:08,940
While our cookies are baking, we are going
to make some decoration details,

48
00:03:08,950 --> 00:03:13,409
These take a long time to set, so if you want
to make these the night before,

49
00:03:13,409 --> 00:03:19,169
you can do that, they take anywhere from 8-12
hours. You want to let them sit at room temperature.

50
00:03:19,169 --> 00:03:23,159
Here I’ve made 2 templates in photoshop,
1 is a bunch of Horde symbols, and

51
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:26,699
1 is a bunch of Alliance symbols, I’ll put
a link down below so if you want to use

52
00:03:26,699 --> 00:03:28,639
these templates that I’ve made, you can!

53
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:31,129
Or if you’d like to make your own you can
do that as well.

54
00:03:31,129 --> 00:03:35,309
I placed the piece of paper down on top of
a cutting board, so I could move it around

55
00:03:35,309 --> 00:03:39,499
if I needed to, and then you’re gonna place
a piece of wax paper, right on top.

56
00:03:39,499 --> 00:03:40,239
And tape it down!

57
00:03:40,239 --> 00:03:44,790
I’m gonna start by piping the Horde symbol
first, and again, I’m using royal icing

58
00:03:44,790 --> 00:03:49,330
that I’ve dyed red, I’ve just placed it
into a plastic baggie with a number 2 tip.

59
00:03:49,330 --> 00:03:54,020
When you're piping htese, Just take your time, I like to pipe the outside of the outline first and then fill

60
00:03:54,029 --> 00:03:56,629
it in. Then move the icing around with a little
toothpick.

61
00:03:56,629 --> 00:04:00,510
Got all of our Horde Designs done, and now
I’m gonna set these off to the side

62
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:03,249
because I don’t want to bump them while
I’m piping the Alliance.

63
00:04:03,249 --> 00:04:06,749
That’s the worst thing! When you’ve piped
all your cute designs and you bump ‘em

64
00:04:06,749 --> 00:04:07,639
with your elbow….

65
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:09,540
I’ve done that…..

66
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:14,499
To pipe our alliance symbols, I’m gonna
be using the yellow royal icing, and again,

67
00:04:14,499 --> 00:04:19,039
I’m using a number 2 tip. I’m gonna be
tracing and filling in all of the white parts

68
00:04:19,039 --> 00:04:23,280
of the design. Once you’re done we’re
gonna let these sit out at room temperature,

69
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:29,490
not in the refrigerator, just at room temperature
for 8-12 hours to completely dry.

70
00:04:29,490 --> 00:04:32,330
While our designs are drying we are gonna
ice our cookies.

71
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:36,180
Our cookies are fresh out of the oven, I’ve
given them plenty of time to cool.

72
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:39,349
You don’t want to ice your cookies while
they’re still warm, otherwise the icing

73
00:04:39,349 --> 00:04:41,990
will goop off, it will just kind of, like,
melt.

74
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:42,720
You don’t want that!

75
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:46,220
We’re gonna be icing 1/2 of them black,
and 1/2 of them blue.

76
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:50,409
I’m gonna start with the black royal icing,
I put it into a plastic baggie with a

77
00:04:50,409 --> 00:04:53,310
number 3 tip. Little bit bigger this time.

78
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:56,690
And we’re gonna pipe an outline, all the
way around the cookie.

79
00:04:56,690 --> 00:05:00,520
Now for the blue, we’re gonna do the same
thing, pipe an outline all the way

80
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:03,449
around our cookie. Next we are going to flood
our cookies.

81
00:05:03,449 --> 00:05:06,659
Flooding is just when you fill in the cookie.
So I like to make zig-zags,

82
00:05:06,659 --> 00:05:11,069
I go back and forth. Then I'm gonna take
a toothpick to just smooth out the icing.

83
00:05:11,069 --> 00:05:13,500
Then you’re gonna do this to the rest of
your cookies!

84
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,270
Once you’ve iced all of your cookies we’re
gonna let them sit out for about 10-20

85
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:21,479
minutes to set. Final step, it is time to
assemble our cookies!

86
00:05:21,479 --> 00:05:25,840
I’m going to be placing our red Horde designs
on top of our black cookies.

87
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:29,939
And, our Alliance designs on top of our blue
cookies!

88
00:05:29,939 --> 00:05:34,460
Over here I’ve got our designs, they have
dried, what I like to do is take a pair of

89
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:38,370
scissors, cut them out, don’t bend them,
and then with 1 of the shapes I’m gonna

90
00:05:38,370 --> 00:05:41,039
very carefully, I like to get down here.

91
00:05:41,039 --> 00:05:42,550
Get even shorter!

92
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:47,450
Using the edge of the table to gently remove
the design from the wax paper.

93
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:51,440
And I’m gonna be using a sharp cutting knife,
like this, to catch it.

94
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:53,920
Gently pick it up and place it on top of your
cookie.

95
00:05:53,930 --> 00:05:58,710
If you don’t want to deal with a sharp cutting knife
you can use a small off-set spatula,

96
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:03,909
You gotta go really fast, you press down your
spatula, and shoot it underneath!

97
00:06:03,909 --> 00:06:06,169
It’s real fast, like a ninja!

98
00:06:06,490 --> 00:06:08,759
Lift, and transfer!

99
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:12,870
Last detail, I almost forgot, we’re gonna
pipe the Lion’s little nose!

100
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:17,479
Over here I’ve switched to a number 1 tip,
just a little triangle right there,

101
00:06:17,479 --> 00:06:20,090
and we’re gonna do this to the rest of our
cookies.

102
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:21,640
Ta-da!

103
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:26,520
Here are the traditional Warcraft Horde and
Alliance themed cookies that we made today!

104
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,879
Whether you are for the Horde! Or for the
Alliance!

105
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:34,080
We’ve got some yummy treats! And a big thank
you to you guys for suggesting something

106
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:37,919
Warcraft themed, these were very fun and easy
to make!

107
00:06:37,919 --> 00:06:41,969
I’ll be taking lots of pictures of these
cookies and posting them on Facebook,

108
00:06:41,969 --> 00:06:46,889
Twitter, Tumblr and Instagram! And if you
guys make any themed Warcraft treats,

109
00:06:46,889 --> 00:06:50,840
please take a picture and send it to me! I
love seeing your baking creations,

110
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:53,300
I just get a big kick out of it. It makes
my day!

111
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:57,539
And, if you have any other ideas for any other
Nerdy Nummies, please let me know

112
00:06:57,539 --> 00:07:00,479
leave me a comment down below and I will do
my best to make it happen.

113
00:07:00,479 --> 00:07:02,079
Alright, thanks again, bye-bye!

[GILMORE]
How did a plastered, or-der-less, party of gits,
with no patience, a tendency to break shit, go on and save

Tal’Dorei’s revolutionary heroes.

Vex’ahlia and Vax’ildan, whose Father couldn’t bother,

Pike Trickfoot, a cleric, little lady is a monstah!

-but wait we can’t forget the bardster,

Scanlan Shorthalt, I’m a gnome

(Pike’s-great) great grandfather in trouble outside of Westruun

[ENSEMBLE] (whisper)
She nurses Grog to health,
But the herd is in the wind.

Keyleth felt a smother, her mother lost on a sacred trial
Left her with a destiny to unite the Ashari tribe
(her people said) “Keyleth’s gotta lead us, it’s her turn”

[GILMORE and (ENSEMBLE)]
They wouldn’t have made it far

journeyin’ together as the SHITS
Tradin’ out pain and sufferin’, for problems they could fix
(Scammin’) for every gold piece Vex had her eye on
(Plannin’) for the future, see Greyskull outside of Emon? (oooh)
Symbol     of-a-group headed for wealth and true fame
For-the-future, they should really consider a new name…

[VOX MACHINA]
In Emon we’ll make up a new name (Just you wait)
In Emon we’ll take up a new name (Just you wait)
For Emon we’ll take up a new name


[COMPANY, WOMEN]
For Emon

[COMPANY, MEN]
Emon

[GILMORE]
Just you wait

[ENSEMBLE 1]            [ENSEMBLE 2]
The party called Vox Machina    (party called Vox Machina)
Fate is pulling the strings for you    (fate is pulling the strings)
You could never back down
You never learned to take your time
The, party called Vox Machina    (party called Vox Machina)
When Exandria sings of you
Will they know what you overcame?
Will they know you rewrote the game?
The world will never be the same, oh

[ALLURA]                            [ENSEMBLE]
There’s heroes in the city now, see if you can spot ‘em,    (just you wait)
Adventurers we celebrate, climbin’ up from the bottom
Their enemies know well their name, their backs, allies’ve got ‘em

[KIMA / ALLURA / GILMORE]
We fought with them


[KIMA / ALLURA]
We would die for them

[KIMA]
Me? I trusted them

[ALLURA]
Me? I loved them

[GILMORE] (casual, talking delivery)
And me?
I’m the damn fool that sponsored ‘em


[VOX MACHINA]
There’s a million things we haven’t done
But just you wait


[GILMORE]
What’s your name?


[VOX MACHINA]
We’re the party called Vox Machina!

title: Crafts With Sharpies | Tay from Millennial Moms
description:
Today's DIY is crafts with sharpies! Sharpies work great for being permanent but they also have a chemical makeup that makes them fun to use for these cool projects. Tie dye shirts and removable labels are really fun and super easy to create.

I'm Tay from Millennial Moms and I post DIY projects every Tuesday!

Don't miss out, subscribe to Millennial Moms!
http://www.youtube.com/c/MillennialMoms?sub_confirmation=1
_

Follow Tay!
Main Channel: http://www.youtube.com/tetetakneea
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/auntie_tay
Twitter: http://twitter.com/AuntTeTay
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/2kidsandlosingit
_

Follow Millennial Moms!
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/MillennialMoms
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/Millennial-Moms-1635417593373385/?fref=ts
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/MillennialMomsOfficial
_

Created by Millennial Moms for Millennial Moms! We are the online home for smart, savvy women who want to share, learn, explore, and     laugh about all the real-life moments that make us "moms"! 

Tune in daily Monday-Saturday at 10 am (CST) to find videos on food, DIY, lifestyle, beauty, fashion, advice, tips and much more!
_

FTC disclosure: This is not a sponsored video.

title: TOTALLY NOT GAY! BORUTO (Cosplay Parody) 2017 Update - EP1
description:
This is a re-upload of our 1st episode Naruto Cosplay Skit! 
YouTube blocked and copyrighted the previous video so instead, we just decided on uploading a new version that's family friendly and copyright free! :D
Thank you all for the love and support!

This video is a parody/spoof of the original Boruto movie and is sort of a remake of a few of the original scenes. We wanted to poke fun at our favorite characters in this hilarious cosplay skit.

title: Pasta Dinner | Mealtime with Bella & Beans | Encourage Children to Eat
description:
It's dinner time! Bella and Beans are eating pasta for their dinner, and they would love you and your children to join them.  They hope to encourage your kids to eat. Of course there is also some learning too, today they discover the planets of our solar system. 

Fun Original Children's Songs We Love: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLbQpjCtCgwen9QFBqZ1cVflOLkLQ0BLVB

If you enjoyed this meal then why not take a look at some of our other videos: 
👉   https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLbQpjCtCgwens_yUHw87WwtI0i9Dm_RlY

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Dear Parents,  Bella & Beans are here to help.  

Our Mission
We want to make Mum and Dad's life much easier by providing quality, educational, and highly entertaining content for tiny tots everywhere. Feel free to tell us what you would like to see and hear from Bella and Beans, whether it's a classic nursery rhyme or an original song to help with your child's routine.  

Thanks for watching, don't forget to SUBSCRIBE.

We are now on Instagram and would love you to join us
👉 www.instagram.com/Bella_and_Beans 👈

A great resource for information and support check out https://www.mumsnet.com/

Catch you later Bella and Beans! x💗 x

Feel free to drop us a message
singalongkids123@gmail.com

title: Berserk: Guts Body Paint Cosplay Tutorial (NoBlandMakeup)
description:
Hey guys!

My last body paint of the year :D. This one is also my first manga/anime body paint tutorial. I also got someone to sit still for an hour so I could do it, so bonus points to Mike for being a boss :D.

So what the hell made me want to do this? Mike asked nicely? That's actually basically what happened lol. I'm also trying to get through my long ass list of stuff I said I was going to do this year at some point... it's a really long list. I'm also going to try extra hard to post more regularly and not go on random long ass hiatuses.

So who is Guts? A very complicated individual. Without spoilers (in case anyone wants to watch the show), he's a badass swordsman, with a gigantic sword and a really pissy attitude, granted after watching the show you can't really blame him... yeah without spoilers that's basically all I've got lol.

My next video is going to be my year in review, so if you guys would like to see anything for next year, leave me a comment letting me know!

captions:
1
00:00:21,279 --> 00:00:22,279
Hey guys, so this is Mike.

2
00:00:22,279 --> 00:00:23,279
Mike is about to pretend like he's not about
to have alot of fun.

3
00:00:23,279 --> 00:00:24,279
We shall see!!

4
00:00:24,279 --> 00:00:25,279
Alright, so to start off I just painted his
face white just to give myself a base and

5
00:00:25,279 --> 00:00:27,500
this is going to make my life alot easier
when I decide to go over everything with black

6
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,670
to do line work and stuff.

7
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:30,429
Plus then I on't have to go around everything.

8
00:00:30,429 --> 00:00:38,190
Don't forget to do your ears, and any part
of your neck that will definitely for sure

9
00:00:38,190 --> 00:00:40,680
be white.

10
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:53,730
Also don't forget your eyelids and stuff.

11
00:00:53,730 --> 00:01:00,629
Then I went in and filled in his eyes... eyebrows,
with black body paint and just started shaping

12
00:01:00,629 --> 00:01:07,290
them like Guts in the picture that I will
have linked somewhere... probably down below!

13
00:01:07,290 --> 00:01:08,630
Check it out!

14
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:12,130
I also started messing with his eye shape
and basically adding a little bit of detail

15
00:01:12,130 --> 00:01:13,360
so he looks more manga-y.

16
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:16,310
This is actually my first manga body paint
thing, and it was...

17
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:23,450
I think it came out pretty cool so yeah.

18
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:33,740
I didn't do too much shading right now just
because I was kind of going to go with it

19
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:35,790
and see how it looked, and also I was going
to change some stuff later so don't worry

20
00:01:35,790 --> 00:01:36,790
about it :D.

21
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:37,790
Now Guts has some pointy spikey bangs.

22
00:01:37,790 --> 00:01:38,920
I went ahead and did those first and then
I worried about painting the rest of his hair.

23
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:39,920
I just wanted to get that shape first.

24
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:43,409
Also make sure that when you are connecting
everything that you make it look a little

25
00:01:43,409 --> 00:01:47,399
more fluid than just some weird spikey lines.Also
don't forget to outline your ears and stuff

26
00:01:47,399 --> 00:02:43,670
just like you would for the rest of your face
because that's what the cool kids do.

27
00:02:43,670 --> 00:03:07,217
I then started applying my shading and stuff
and also reshaping- sort of- his mouth.

28
00:03:07,217 --> 00:03:08,217
Guts doesn't smile and when he does it's kind
of creepy.

29
00:03:08,217 --> 00:03:09,217
Then I started working on his neck also shading
in stuff and then drawing in the scarf...

30
00:03:09,217 --> 00:03:10,960
bandanna... whatever you want to call it,
thing he had.

31
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:19,380
I didn't worry so much about shading again,
I just wanted to get the shapes right and

32
00:03:19,380 --> 00:03:20,380
all the dark pieces first.

33
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,380
Then I was going to fill everything in with
white, and then do some more shading and stuff.

34
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:22,380
I'm going to say I find when you do more complicated
body paints like this, doing little things

35
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:23,380
at a time actually does help make things alot
easier.

36
00:03:23,380 --> 00:03:26,720
And surprisingly this whole thing, minus breaks
so that I could like walk around and stuff,

37
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,069
took about an hour.

38
00:03:29,069 --> 00:03:34,010
And by the way if you guys like his tattoo,
you can get it- if you're in or near Deerfield,

39
00:03:34,010 --> 00:03:35,593
you can get it done at Wizard's Tattoo, and
I'll have it linked down below.

40
00:03:35,593 --> 00:03:41,330
And I'm really, really sorry that I covered
it, but I had to.

picture.

And I'll see you guys next time!

Bye!

title: Period 101 | Brooklyn and Bailey
description:
Y'all have been requesting a Period 101 video for the longest time, so we did our best to answer the most common period-related questions that you've been asking for!

EVERY woman has a period, has THAT time of month where they go into their menstrual cycle.  While no one would describe it as an absolute joy, there are certainly ways to make it a little less dreadful!  Knowing and understanding how to use the must-have products, such as pads (and the different types of pads), tampons and other products, makes a massive difference.

Hopefully there is some period advice in here that is helpful to you, and make sure to ask your doctor, mom, sister, or anyone close to you in your life when making important decisions around your period.
Don't forget to get our NEW merch, too! http://www.brooklynandbailey.com/shop

_______________________________________________________
Download: http://www.mediafire.com/file/91405y9tbbgzlxu/Senbonzakura_-_Lizz.mp3

It's been a while since I last did a Vocaloid song! I'm planning on doing a few Vocaloid covers these next few weeks, so stay tuned! I loved kran's lyrics, so I had to sing them. Please check out kran's cover here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ov5IyW-O6bg
I hope you guys like it! It's such a beautiful song~

title: DIY DOG TREATS!
description:
In celebration of my French Bulldog Cookie's second birthday, I made these fun and easy DIY dog treats! Happy 2nd Birthday Cookie!

MORE DIY DOG TREATS: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l3Mb9RyW3V4

ORDER MY BAKING LINE: http://bit.ly/BakingLine
Order The Nerdy Nummies Cookbook here: http://www.nerdynummiescookbook.com

FOLLOW ME HERE:
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/rosannapansino
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/RosannaPansino
Tumblr: http://www.rosannapansino.tumblr.com
Instagram: http://instagram.com/rosannapansino
Snapchat: rosannapansino

THE THINGS YOU WILL NEED: 
Mini Mutt Mints
* (1/2) Cup Fresh Minced Parsley
* (1/2) Cup Fresh Minced Mint
* (2) Cups Oat Flour: http://amzn.to/2cNxMsy
* (1/2) Cup Almond Meal: http://amzn.to/2clXL8e
* (1/4) Cup Apple Sauce: http://amzn.to/2ck0Q5t
* (1/4) Cup Coconut Water: http://amzn.to/2chG88q
* (1/4) Cup Coconut Oil: http://amzn.to/2csPbG2
* (1) Heart Cookie Cutter Set: http://amzn.to/2ck1joc

Sweet Potato Doggie Biscuits
* (1/4) Cup Fresh Minced Parsley
* (1/2) Cup Minced Celery
* (3/4) Cup Mashed Sweet Potato
* (1) Cup Brown Rice Flour: http://amzn.to/2c62qu8
* (1/4) Cup Chicken Broth: http://amzn.to/2chGVGo
* (1) Cup Oat Flour: http://amzn.to/2cNxMsy
* (1/2) Teaspoon Chicken Seasoning: http://amzn.to/2chHoJ1
* (1) Bone Cookie Cutter Set: http://amzn.to/2c8Y34x

PB & Carrot Mini Pup Cakes
* (1/4) Cup Shredded Carrots
* (1/2) Cup Ground Oat Flour: http://amzn.to/2cNxMsy
* (1/4) Cup Creamy Peanut Butter: http://amzn.to/2cNwHAM
* (2) Tablespoons Coconut Oil: http://amzn.to/2csPbG2
* (1/4) Cup Applesauce: http://amzn.to/2ck0Q5t
* (2) Tablespoons Honey: http://amzn.to/2c62Tg3
* (1/2) Teaspoon Baking Soda: http://amzn.to/2c1Hnuz
* (1/2) Cup Yogurt
* (1/2) Cup Peanut Butter: http://amzn.to/2cNwHAM

HELPFUL LINKS:
* Cutting Board: http://amzn.to/2cOnmrf
* Potato Masher: http://amzn.to/2c63NcB
* Vegetable Peeler: http://amzn.to/2cLHOpO
* Mini Cupcake Tray: http://amzn.to/2ct4Xkk
* Decorating Bags: http://amzn.to/2ck1XBP
* #22 Decorating Tip: http://amzn.to/2cNxwJP
* Mini Cupcake Liners: http://amzn.to/2c1HExC

This is not a sponsored video. All products purchased by me.

Recently at a barbeque, things started to click for Amanda. She continued on her blog writing QUOTE: we were all playing a fun game of charades and I see Lele get up as I'm telling a joke. I look over my shoulder and see Lele on her phone snapchatting and then realize wait… That's my phone. Take my phone back and my photo was deleted. So I knew it was her at that moment it all made sense."
Amanda then confronted Lele, who eventually came clean… The very next morning when Amanda asked Lele about the situation she replied by saying QUOTE: 'No way we are best friends I would never do that.'  
Amanda then said QUOTE: She came up to my apartment later and I asked her face-to-face and she looked like she was lying and I demanded the truth from her. She admitted to it all. She would even be by my side when I would realize my things been deleted and comforting me saying, 'Oh my goodness good thing I'm here and we are such good friends I will help you with this.' So manipulative."' 
Lele apparently told fans that Amanda deleted her videos first and that is why all of this started but Amanda fired back saying “she’s lying to all of our friends saying how sorry she is for what she did and then going and doing this? She is still trying to ruin me LOL for no reason."
Amanda is also going HAM on twitter retweeting everyone that is showing her support on social media like this photo that was captioned Shame on you @lelepons !!! What you did to @AmandaCerny is soo insane!! #TeamAmanda
While Lele hasn’t spoked out directly on the matter, she has been busy posting messages that seem to be about the drama like this tweet that reads “People will only bring you down when they have nothing to bring them up -my little cousin” https://twitter.com/lelepons/status/775385487666188288 
Hmmmmm, all seems very shady to me… I can’t believe Amanda and Lele were BFF’s and Lele really had it out for Amanda the whole time… DRAMA. Watch your back, kids.
Most importantly I do what to know what all of you are thinking about the internet drama. Who’s side are you on? Can you believe this is a real thing we’re talking about? Let me hear it in the comment section below, then click right here to watch an episode of beauty break with GRACE HELBIG!!! I’m ryland Adams, thanks for watching, see you soon!

title: The Deaths of Chromie Guide - 7.2.5 Scenario
description:
The Deaths of Chromie is a new single-player scenario coming to World of Warcraft: Legion in the upcoming Patch 7.2.5. Doing the Deaths of Chromie will earn you a unique transmog set for your armor type and potentially a bronze whelp pet, but you won't be finishing the Deaths of Chromie on your first attempt. The Chromie Scenario coming in 7.2.5 is designed to be played repeatedly and becomes more attainable as you earn rep and learn more about the attacks orchestrated against Chromie. 

I STRONGLY recommend that you turn on Sound-Dialogue when playing the Deaths of Chromie in 7.2.5 because Chromie's voice acting is something else. The whole Chromie Scenario experience was very fun and I'm excited for it to hit live Legion servers after the patch 7.2.5 release date in June. The time-loop theme of the Deaths of Chromie is very reminiscent of movies like Groundhog Day or the Edge of Tomorrow. I got an almost Dark Souls vibe from the concept of playing an event repeatedly to gain knowledge, perspective and practice. Play the Deaths of Chromie scenario in patch 7.2.5 to save Chromie! Apologies if my voice is a little bit scratchy-I was coming down with a cold. I re-uploaded this video to fix a minor issue with the music volume in the first minute- thanks for your patience! It's otherwise unchanged. 

Let me know what you think and check out my channel for battle pet guides, other WoW videos and a weekly vlog!

Check out my Patreon! I make these videos full time now. Your support and donations keep me going. I can't thank you guys enough for this. http://www.patreon.com/hazelnuttygames 

Find me on Twitter at
 http://www.twitter.com/HazelNuttyGames

Instagram pictures of my irl pets at 
 http://instagram.com/hazelnuttylife
captions:
1
00:00:00,530 --> 00:00:01,530
Hi!

2
00:00:01,530 --> 00:00:05,270
I'm Hazel, and this is a complete guide to
the Deaths of Chromie scenario coming to WoW

3
00:00:05,270 --> 00:00:06,490
in patch 7.2.5.

4
00:00:06,490 --> 00:00:11,799
This video will contain super-duper-mega-spoilers
for the scenario, so if you're avoiding spoilers

5
00:00:11,799 --> 00:00:13,009
you gotta leave right now.

6
00:00:13,009 --> 00:00:17,770
You'll be able to play the scenario on live
servers once patch 7.2.5 releases, most likely

7
00:00:17,770 --> 00:00:19,700
sometime in June.

8
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:23,750
To get started, you Pick up the quest 'The
Day that Chromie Dies' in the Violet Citadel.

9
00:00:23,750 --> 00:00:27,610
I don't see any prerequisites so you should
be able to start right away.

10
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:31,390
This is a repeatable scenario that's designed
to be repeated in order to succeed, sort of

11
00:00:31,390 --> 00:00:32,619
like Withered Army Training.

12
00:00:32,619 --> 00:00:36,100
The whole thing is very Edge of Tomorrow,
Groundhog day.

13
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,010
Your goal in the scenario is to prevent the
death of Chromie that she has foreseen for

14
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:41,390
herself at Wyrmrest Temple.

15
00:00:41,390 --> 00:00:45,390
To 'win' the scenario, you need to prevent
eight different attacks on Chromie, all within

16
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:47,420
the fifteen minute timer.

17
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:50,781
Each time you try, you'll earn rep with Chromie
that allows you to buff her at the start of

18
00:00:50,781 --> 00:00:51,890
the scenario.

19
00:00:51,890 --> 00:00:54,940
You'll need to first tackle attacks at the
four Dragonshrines in order to unlock the

20
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:56,460
other four attacks.

21
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,649
Your first runthrough of each Dragonshrine
involves a one-time-only questline, and completing

22
00:01:00,649 --> 00:01:04,280
the shrine is expedited every time after that.

23
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:08,630
It is literally not humanly possible to win
the scenario on your first try, so don't worry

24
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:09,920
about making it all the way.

25
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:14,479
In the instance, your player level is scaled
to 112 and your item level is scaled to 1000,

26
00:01:14,479 --> 00:01:17,320
so you don't need to worry too much about
your gear.

27
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:20,409
Your legendaries and set bonuses do still
function like normal, though, so wear your

28
00:01:20,409 --> 00:01:22,690
best damage set.

29
00:01:22,690 --> 00:01:26,650
While the first four dragonshrines are much
faster on subsequent tries, unfortunately

30
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:31,170
it looks like the second half of the attacks
is the same each time you attempt the scenario.

31
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:34,590
That means that even with all four shrines
prepared ahead of time, you're going to need

32
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:38,740
both buffs and practice to finish before our
favourite little gnome dragon eats it.

33
00:01:38,740 --> 00:01:42,790
As you do stuff in the scenario, you'll earn
rep directly with Chromie.

34
00:01:42,790 --> 00:01:46,960
You start off as a WHELPLING and eventually
work your way up to a chrono lord.

35
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:50,530
You'll need increasingly higher levels of
rep in order to research new talents for Chromie

36
00:01:50,530 --> 00:01:52,469
to use as she aids you in the instance.

37
00:01:52,469 --> 00:01:56,490
You will absolutely need those talents to
finish, and there are lengthy research times

38
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:58,030
associated with the later tiers.

39
00:01:58,030 --> 00:02:01,890
As it stands, nobody's going to be finishing
this on day 1.

40
00:02:01,890 --> 00:02:05,399
Chromie rep appears to only be relevant for
those talents, so once you're done with the

41
00:02:05,399 --> 00:02:07,479
scenario there's no more reason to grind it.

42
00:02:07,479 --> 00:02:10,879
Well, not unless you're one of those people
that needs EVERY rep on your pane capped,

43
00:02:10,879 --> 00:02:12,860
in which case knock yourself out.

44
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:16,659
We'll take a look at Chromie's talents in
detail later in this guide.

45
00:02:16,659 --> 00:02:21,310
You can do the four dragonshrines in any order,
but the first one I swung by was the Emerald

46
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:22,310
Dragonshrine.

47
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:26,160
Kill owls and lashers to collect Fibers and
Plumes, which you combine to create a Nightmare

48
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,160
Catcher.

49
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:31,600
Use that near an Ancient to enter the nightmare
and kill the oogly booglys who are oogling

50
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,600
him.

51
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,480
Repeat that process three times and you'll
find out about a Satyr boss by the dragon

52
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:37,160
palm at the lake.

53
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,489
Go kill him and the green shrine is done.

54
00:02:39,489 --> 00:02:42,710
On future attempts, you can go right to the
Satyr without having to boogle the ooglies

55
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,530
all over again.

56
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:48,010
The red dragonshrine is under attack from
three types of Undead.

57
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:51,590
Kill the three leaders to collect a Soul Crystal
Fragment from each, and combine those to get

58
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,950
your next step.

59
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:56,241
To the surprise of nobody, the soul crystal
sends you into the base of the tree to kill

60
00:02:56,241 --> 00:02:57,241
a Lich.

61
00:02:57,241 --> 00:03:01,090
The next time you come back here, you can
just fly right into the tree and get him.

62
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:04,879
The Azure dragonshrine has a bunch of mana-creature
shenanigans as usual.

63
00:03:04,879 --> 00:03:08,860
Kill fiends and wyrms to collect 50 Darkened
Scraps of Vellum, which send you up to kill

64
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:10,689
a voidlord boss on the floating platform.

65
00:03:10,689 --> 00:03:14,349
The next time you do it, fly straight to the
platform.

66
00:03:14,349 --> 00:03:18,580
The Obsidian Dragonshrine has our old pal
Wrathion to chat with, which is kind of intriguing.

67
00:03:18,580 --> 00:03:22,879
You go into the shrine and fight your way
to the very end to kill a big fiery boneshard

68
00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:23,959
boss.

69
00:03:23,959 --> 00:03:27,480
After that, you learn that there's a sneaky
dreadlord outside to the right of the cave

70
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,480
entrance.

71
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:31,470
Kill him, and next time you're here you can
skip straight to him.

72
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:35,291
All the Dragonshrine bosses are present but
invisible on future attempts, so you need

73
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:39,150
to remember where they are and go stand on
them to reveal them.

74
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:42,739
Your first victory against the green shrine
Satyr will give you a Chronoshard unlocking

75
00:03:42,739 --> 00:03:43,970
a portal to Andorhal.

76
00:03:43,970 --> 00:03:48,629
You find a version of Chromie trapped in the
inn, unable to leave because of the big Horde

77
00:03:48,629 --> 00:03:49,629
cannon.

78
00:03:49,629 --> 00:03:52,250
Maybe Horde players deal with an Alliance
cannon, who knows.

79
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:56,190
Either way you need to take it out, and you
can't just walk up to it and kill it.

80
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:57,379
Believe me, I tried.

81
00:03:57,379 --> 00:04:01,640
There are four horde captains in Andorhal-
kill each of them and loot items from them

82
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,650
that will help you kill the cannon.

83
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:07,260
Using all of the items will remove both of
the Cannon's buffs and take it down to a quarter

84
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:09,600
health, at which point you can kill it.

85
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:13,630
Your first time through the Blue shrine get
you a Chronoshard for the Mount Hyjal portal.

86
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:16,609
Right ahead, we've got an injured Chromie
hanging out on the ground.

87
00:04:16,609 --> 00:04:20,560
Stay by her side and defeat waves of enemies
as quickly as possible to rescue her and defend

88
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,250
the attack.

89
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:25,930
The Ruby shrine boss gives you a chronoshard
to take you back to Strathholme.

90
00:04:25,930 --> 00:04:29,770
You arrive right before Arthas does, and we
know how this story goes.

91
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,180
This is by far the most emotional part of
the scenario.

92
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:36,490
You pick up a quest from Emery in an inn,
and run around picking up items from vendors

93
00:04:36,490 --> 00:04:39,720
in a questline to protect orphans and help
out Emery's crush.

94
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:43,110
He gives you a key, at which point the citizens
you were helpling have turned to undead and

95
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:45,340
you need to escape through the town hall.

96
00:04:45,340 --> 00:04:54,630
Chromie's voice acting comes off as particularly
insensitive at this point.

97
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:58,180
I found it hilarious but I may be a bad person.

98
00:04:58,180 --> 00:05:01,960
Now, fight your way through Stratholme following
the same route you take in the Caverns of

99
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:02,960
time dungeon.

100
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:06,420
Up the stairs, through the bookcase, and down
the street to where we used to fight Mal'ganis.

101
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:11,740
He's not around, but Nezar'Azret is holding
down the fort so go ahead and kill her instead.

102
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:15,420
This whole shard took me right up to the fifteen
minute mark, all by itself.

103
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:18,789
You would think that on future attempts you
would still have the friggin key to skip ahead

104
00:05:18,789 --> 00:05:21,910
to the town hall but nope, you gotta start
from scratch.

105
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:23,430
That's gonna suck.

106
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:26,970
The Dreadlord outside the Black shrine gives
you the final chronoshard portal to take you

107
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:28,120
to the Well of Eternity.

108
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:32,850
Here, just fight your way through the dungeon
like you did in Cataclysm, only backwards.

109
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:36,840
If it's been a while or you never did this
one, just check out my handy map.

110
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:40,830
Reach the beginning of the dungeon to defend
the final attack.

111
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:45,570
Presumably doing all 8 bosses within 15 minutes
wins, but there's no way in heck that you're

112
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:48,660
doing that without some or all of Chromie's
talents.

113
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:51,900
Her upgrades function a lot like Class Order
Hall research.

114
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:55,761
Each new tier requires a new level of reputation
with Chromie, and starting with tier 3 there

115
00:05:55,761 --> 00:05:59,410
are some significant research times before
the buff can take effect.

116
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:02,870
On tier 1, you choose between Time Stop and
Acceleration.

117
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:05,830
Either one gives you a bonus 5% damage and
healing.

118
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:09,900
The enemies aren't too difficult to handle,
so I recommend taking Acceleration for a base

119
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,950
20% to mounted and movement speed.

120
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,330
You're gonna need it.

121
00:06:13,330 --> 00:06:17,490
On tier 2, we have Accelerated Aggression
to turn Chromie into a tank, or Rapid Recovery

122
00:06:17,490 --> 00:06:18,960
to make her a healer.

123
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:23,889
Either choice gives you a bonus 5% health,
and most specs will want to choose Rapid Recovery.

124
00:06:23,889 --> 00:06:27,720
On tier 3, we have Dragon's Determination
or Chrono Charisma.

125
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:31,789
Determination reduces Chromie's damage taken
by 20%, while Charisma gives you increased

126
00:06:31,789 --> 00:06:34,240
reputation gain in the later minutes of the
scenario.

127
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:38,020
If Chromie dies, you get kicked out regardless
of how much time you had.

128
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:41,900
The rep gain sounds really good at first,
but as you do the scenario you'll find yourself

129
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:46,389
often leaving early once you know you don't
have enough time to get to another objective.

130
00:06:46,389 --> 00:06:50,190
You're also more likely to be bottlenecked
by research speed than rep, so I went with

131
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:52,849
Dragon's Determination to keep Chromie extra
safe.

132
00:06:52,849 --> 00:06:56,000
Either way you get a bonus 5% speed.

133
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,860
On tier 4, we have Insight or Blessing of
the Bronze Dragonflight.

134
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:03,301
Insight lets you track nearby time chests
on your map, which can contain Sands of Time

135
00:07:03,301 --> 00:07:04,870
for useful buffs.

136
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:08,250
The Blessing improves your Sands of TIme to
grant you Bronze Drakes more often.

137
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:12,259
The Bronze Drake buff allows you to instantly
clear a dragonshrine without going there,

138
00:07:12,259 --> 00:07:14,460
which will rapidly speed up your run.

139
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:17,600
The tier 4 bonus is 10% damage and healing.

140
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:22,250
Tier 5 is a single talent, increasing the
drop rate of Sands of Time by 100%.

141
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:26,520
We'll take a closer look at exactly what Sands
do next, but trust me when I say that that's

142
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,930
really juicy.

143
00:07:27,930 --> 00:07:29,470
You'll also get 10% more health.

144
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:34,010
Tier 6 has you choose between Infinite Velocity
and Continous Keepsakes.

145
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:38,319
Velocity gives you portals to the shrines,
cutting travel time out of the equation.

146
00:07:38,319 --> 00:07:41,479
Keepsakes increases the chance for you to
get an item that instantly clears a specific

147
00:07:41,479 --> 00:07:44,880
one of the four chronoshard attacks from your
Sands of Time.

148
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:48,550
When combined with the extra Sands from Tier
5 and all the movement speed we've collected,

149
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:50,409
Keepsakes seems better.

150
00:07:50,409 --> 00:07:54,599
Those second attacks, Stratholme in particular
are huge timesinks and getting an insta-clear

151
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:57,759
or three is the only way you're going to make
it on time.

152
00:07:57,759 --> 00:08:00,449
The bonus here is yet another 10% speed.

153
00:08:00,449 --> 00:08:05,639
The final buff requires Chrono Lord rep, and
takes a whopping 5 days to research.

154
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:09,670
Chromie can summon a dragon that crashes into
your foes, hopefully dealing a substantial

155
00:08:09,670 --> 00:08:10,670
amount of damage.

156
00:08:10,670 --> 00:08:15,600
At this point you get a bonus 50% to damage,
healing, health and speed so if you haven't

157
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,650
won the scenario already you should be able
to now.

158
00:08:18,650 --> 00:08:22,860
The Sands of Time drop from mobs, bosses and
you can get a quest to get extras from doing

159
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:25,500
a specific shrine boss each run.

160
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:29,919
Use them to gain one of two buffs that are
randomly selected from the following list

161
00:08:29,919 --> 00:08:36,080
Get 25% rep gain, 10% damage, take 10% reduced
damage, get 10% run speed, extend the scenario

162
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:40,670
duration, auto-complete a dragonshrine or
auto-complete a specific portal challenge.

163
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:44,850
These buffs stack and you'll get quite a few
Sands, so do the quicker challenges first

164
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,430
so you have more buffs for the longer ones.

165
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:52,150
Sands can also grant you a pouch with 30ish
gold, which is a bit of a slap in the face.

166
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:55,430
If you know you're not on a success attempt
and you're just grinding rep or unlocking

167
00:08:55,430 --> 00:08:57,230
a shrine boss, go for it.

168
00:08:57,230 --> 00:09:00,380
Last, you can get 10 timewarped badges for
you to keep.

169
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:03,580
Take the badges if you're on a throwaway attempt,
and stack up the buffs if you're trying to

170
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:05,160
seriously make it.

171
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:08,650
It's very cool to have an alternate source
of Timewarped badges outside of timewalking,

172
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:12,440
and I hope there's some reason to repeat the
scenario now and then even after the first

173
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,440
time you win.

174
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:17,130
With the exception of the last two these buffs
are only in effect for your current run of

175
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:21,310
the Deaths of Chromie, and you cannot stockpile
Sands to use in a future run.

176
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:25,730
Due to the research time of Chromie's talents,
I was not able to win the scenario on the

177
00:09:25,730 --> 00:09:26,730
PTR.

178
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:29,080
When you do win, though, there are some rewards
up for grabs.

179
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:33,170
You'll earn a unique set of transmog for your
armor type, shown here.

180
00:09:33,170 --> 00:09:36,070
The cloth in particular looks nice, thanks
Blizz.

181
00:09:36,070 --> 00:09:40,740
There's also a mysterious bronze Test Dragon
pet in the 7.2.5 ptr pet journal, which could

182
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:42,810
be from finishing or an achievement.

183
00:09:42,810 --> 00:09:47,010
My guess is that the whelp is from finishing
your Chromie rep grind and becoming a Chrono-Lord.

184
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:51,200
You'll get some artifact power tokens throughout
the whole questline as well, so I'd say it's

185
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,270
worth doing for most people.

186
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:55,370
So, that is the Deaths of Chromie!

187
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:58,910
It's a fun experience, and I think it has
just enough time-gating to be nicely paced.

188
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:02,800
It took me about 2 to three hours of gameplay
to complete all eight attacks at least once

189
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,430
and then get held up by the talent research
time.

190
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:08,890
You can probably do it faster because I just
told you everything.

191
00:10:08,890 --> 00:10:09,890
Thanks for watching!

192
00:10:09,890 --> 00:10:13,060
Let me know what you think, please consider
leaving a like if you made it this far through

193
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:15,800
listening to me talk and have a wonderful,
wonderful day.

194
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,500
Bye!

and surprise the kids,
and like, A, it's Sunday

359
00:10:49,424 --> 00:10:51,145
and almost all the 
stores are closed,

360
00:10:51,145 --> 00:10:52,787
and B, the two stores we went to

361
00:10:52,787 --> 00:10:54,713
literally only had a Yamaha.

362
00:10:54,713 --> 00:10:55,546
That's all they had,

363
00:10:55,546 --> 00:10:56,597
which I'm not saying
anything against Yamaha,

364
00:10:56,597 --> 00:10:59,136
but I kinda wanted to have
the kids sit on each one,

365
00:10:59,136 --> 00:11:00,693
get a feel for 
which one's like, taller,

366
00:11:00,693 --> 00:11:02,947
which one, the seat 
feels better, right?

367
00:11:02,947 --> 00:11:04,709
Get some competition with
the prices and whatnot.

368
00:11:04,709 --> 00:11:06,963
And like, nothing.

369
00:11:06,963 --> 00:11:09,466
So we definitely 
have to come back.

370
00:11:09,466 --> 00:11:11,023
We definitely have 
to go during the week

371
00:11:11,023 --> 00:11:12,007
when all the 
other shops are open.

372
00:11:12,007 --> 00:11:13,235
I definitely want to
check out North Valley,

373
00:11:13,235 --> 00:11:14,998
'cause North Valley's gonna
have Kawasakis and Hondas,

374
00:11:14,998 --> 00:11:17,008
which are my two leading
brands that I want the kids

375
00:11:17,008 --> 00:11:18,486
to possibly get.

376
00:11:18,486 --> 00:11:20,538
It would be nice if 
we all rode Kawasakis,

377
00:11:20,538 --> 00:11:22,793
but Hondas are a close second.

378
00:11:22,793 --> 00:11:23,626
So, yeah.

379
00:11:23,626 --> 00:11:25,171
Sorry, guys.

380
00:11:25,171 --> 00:11:26,568
Fail dirt bike shopping.

381
00:11:26,568 --> 00:11:27,401
(blows raspberry)

382
00:11:27,401 --> 00:11:29,113
Alright, guys, so we
made our way back home.

383
00:11:29,113 --> 00:11:30,672
Tiff and I kinda talked a little bit,

384
00:11:30,672 --> 00:11:34,276
and we'll probably have to
wait 'til after our trip,

385
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:35,915
which we're going 
on a trip this week,

386
00:11:35,915 --> 00:11:37,227
in case you didn't know.

387
00:11:37,227 --> 00:11:38,087
I kinda hinted at that.

388
00:11:38,087 --> 00:11:39,399
We have an action-packed week,

389
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,300
you guys don't want to miss it.

390
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,283
I mean, like, seriously.

391
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:42,116
It's gonna be awesome.

392
00:11:42,116 --> 00:11:43,127
I've never been to this place.

393
00:11:43,127 --> 00:11:44,710
But anyways,

394
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:47,168
we'll have to wait 'til we
come back after our trip

395
00:11:47,168 --> 00:11:49,544
to go back and look 
at the dirt bikes,

396
00:11:49,544 --> 00:11:50,814
but I'm feeling pretty good.

397
00:11:50,814 --> 00:11:52,083
The research I've done,

398
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:52,916
like I said, it's gonna be

399
00:11:52,916 --> 00:11:53,854
between the Kawasaki 
and the Honda.

400
00:11:53,854 --> 00:11:56,475
I just want the kids 
to sit on them first.

401
00:11:56,475 --> 00:11:58,524
So after our trip,

402
00:11:58,524 --> 00:11:59,962
stay tuned.

403
00:11:59,962 --> 00:12:02,299
New dirt bike for 
one of these kids.

404
00:12:02,299 --> 00:12:03,816
I don't know which one yet.

405
00:12:03,816 --> 00:12:06,029
I'll buy it and then
whoever's my favorite,

406
00:12:06,029 --> 00:12:06,972
I'll give them the bike.

407
00:12:06,972 --> 00:12:08,557
Anyways,

408
00:12:08,557 --> 00:12:09,390
I'm joking, by the way.

409
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,300
I don't have a favorite,
I don't have favorites.

410
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,775
We're gonna play some
Magic: The Gathering.

411
00:12:11,775 --> 00:12:12,679
These kids are super excited,

412
00:12:12,679 --> 00:12:13,694
I built their decks yesterday,

413
00:12:13,694 --> 00:12:15,499
and that's all that's 
been on their mind,

414
00:12:15,499 --> 00:12:17,137
other than the dirt bike,

415
00:12:17,137 --> 00:12:17,970
is to play.

416
00:12:17,970 --> 00:12:21,118
So we've got our decks shuffled,

417
00:12:21,118 --> 00:12:23,088
and our seven cards dealt.

418
00:12:23,088 --> 00:12:23,921
So here we go.

419
00:12:23,921 --> 00:12:25,056
Magic: The Gathering.

420
00:12:25,056 --> 00:12:27,356
Alright, we're well into the game.

421
00:12:27,356 --> 00:12:29,570
And I just told the kids,
put their hands on the table

422
00:12:29,570 --> 00:12:31,297
so that I can kinda 
see what they have

423
00:12:31,297 --> 00:12:32,854
and kinda walk them through
the different steps,

424
00:12:32,854 --> 00:12:34,084
'cause there's a lot to this game.

425
00:12:34,084 --> 00:12:35,560
There's sorcery, 
there's creatures,

426
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:39,022
there's enchantments, 
there's instants.

427
00:12:39,022 --> 00:12:41,152
So it's one of those things
where they're learning.

428
00:12:41,152 --> 00:12:42,425
They're learning.

429
00:12:42,425 --> 00:12:43,909
So far, so good?

430
00:12:43,909 --> 00:12:45,668
What do you think?

431
00:12:45,668 --> 00:12:47,429
You getting bored yet?

432
00:12:47,429 --> 00:12:49,477
It's a slow game.

433
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:51,510
- We're in the learning part,

434
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:52,445
so.

435
00:12:52,445 --> 00:12:53,347
- [Clintus] It's like school.

436
00:12:53,347 --> 00:12:54,741
You're like, meh, school.

437
00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:56,422
- And this is one 
of my creatures.

438
00:12:56,422 --> 00:12:57,364
- That's one of your creatures.

439
00:12:57,364 --> 00:12:59,129
That's a dried cherry, don't eat it.

440
00:12:59,129 --> 00:13:01,792
Alright, so after the first round,

441
00:13:01,792 --> 00:13:03,625
Bryce took out Sierra.

442
00:13:04,705 --> 00:13:05,951
So you eliminated Sierra,

443
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:07,181
and then I eliminated Bryce.

444
00:13:07,181 --> 00:13:08,983
And the reason why I
eliminated Bryce is why?

445
00:13:08,983 --> 00:13:09,966
- I made a mistake,

446
00:13:09,966 --> 00:13:14,766
so I tapped all three of these cards

447
00:13:14,766 --> 00:13:16,281
and I did two damage to Sierra,

448
00:13:16,281 --> 00:13:17,223
so that knocked her out,

449
00:13:17,223 --> 00:13:19,435
then I did three damage to you.

450
00:13:19,435 --> 00:13:20,606
- [Clintus] But, because you tapped

451
00:13:20,606 --> 00:13:21,958
all your creatures, what?

452
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:23,024
- I couldn't block,

453
00:13:23,024 --> 00:13:25,632
so when he has a creature
that I could do six--

454
00:13:25,632 --> 00:13:29,486
- He only had six life,
I had four creatures out

455
00:13:29,486 --> 00:13:32,272
and three of them 
could do enough damage

456
00:13:32,272 --> 00:13:33,257
to kill him out,

457
00:13:33,257 --> 00:13:34,693
let alone all of them together.

458
00:13:34,693 --> 00:13:36,167
So the lesson he learned

459
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:38,299
was don't attack 
with all your creatures

460
00:13:38,299 --> 00:13:39,322
when you have that low of life,

461
00:13:39,322 --> 00:13:40,757
'cause you have 
nothing to block with.

462
00:13:40,757 --> 00:13:43,505
And what are you doing
while we're playing Magic?

463
00:13:43,505 --> 00:13:44,816
- This.

464
00:13:44,816 --> 00:13:45,761
- [Clintus] You're still
playing Best Fiends.

465
00:13:45,761 --> 00:13:46,720
- Yeah, it's so addicting.

466
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,878
- [Clintus] What level are you on?

467
00:13:47,878 --> 00:13:49,968
- Well, I got stuck, like at 47,

468
00:13:49,968 --> 00:13:51,900
then you have to 
do this special thing

469
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:54,607
that has like 20 things within it.

470
00:13:54,607 --> 00:13:55,922
But it's addicting.

471
00:13:55,922 --> 00:13:56,839
- Yeah, 47?

472
00:13:57,696 --> 00:13:59,459
Alright, so after two games,

473
00:13:59,459 --> 00:14:00,376
I won both.

474
00:14:01,331 --> 00:14:02,315
- Obviously.

475
00:14:02,315 --> 00:14:03,669
- Well, no, I mean,

476
00:14:03,669 --> 00:14:05,144
the first game you had me down

477
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:06,661
to like, nine?

478
00:14:06,661 --> 00:14:07,645
I was down low,

479
00:14:07,645 --> 00:14:09,902
but the real 
question is this, okay?

480
00:14:09,902 --> 00:14:10,735
And honestly.

481
00:14:10,735 --> 00:14:13,347
No b.s., you two, okay?

482
00:14:13,347 --> 00:14:14,248
Did you like the game

483
00:14:14,248 --> 00:14:16,381
and do you wanna play it again?

484
00:14:16,381 --> 00:14:17,303
- [Bryce] Yes.
- Yes.

485
00:14:17,303 --> 00:14:19,025
- Yes, both of you?

486
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:21,646
- Can we do tournaments,
like at that one place?

487
00:14:21,646 --> 00:14:23,205
- Well, once you know how to play,

488
00:14:23,205 --> 00:14:26,400
once I know that
you can play by yourself,

489
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,465
and I don't have
to give you any help,

490
00:14:27,465 --> 00:14:28,298
then you can play tournaments.

491
00:14:28,298 --> 00:14:29,169
- Yeah, I meant that,

492
00:14:29,169 --> 00:14:30,727
not like right now.

493
00:14:30,727 --> 00:14:31,560
- You, I was worried, though.

494
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:33,349
It felt like you were getting bored.

495
00:14:33,349 --> 00:14:35,029
Is it because that last
game was just really slow?

496
00:14:35,029 --> 00:14:36,631
- Yeah, like we didn't get any land

497
00:14:36,631 --> 00:14:38,187
so we can put anything--

498
00:14:38,187 --> 00:14:39,292
- The way Magic works, guys,

499
00:14:39,292 --> 00:14:40,850
is you draw seven cards,

500
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:41,916
you have seven 
cards in your hand,

501
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,515
and if you don't 
have any lands,

502
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:44,626
you can't do anything.

503
00:14:44,626 --> 00:14:45,486
And then once you have lands,

504
00:14:45,486 --> 00:14:46,554
you have to have things to do,

505
00:14:46,554 --> 00:14:47,742
and Bryce wasn't 
getting any creatures.

506
00:14:47,742 --> 00:14:48,575
That was your other problem.

507
00:14:48,575 --> 00:14:49,683
You had all spells and instances.

508
00:14:49,683 --> 00:14:51,433
- So what I was doing

509
00:14:56,163 --> 00:14:57,613
was I was getting no land,

510
00:14:57,613 --> 00:14:59,663
but I was getting a
whole lot of creatures.

511
00:14:59,663 --> 00:15:01,196
Then I got a whole bunch of land--

512
00:15:01,196 --> 00:15:03,616
- And no creatures.
- [Bryce] And no creatures.

513
00:15:03,616 --> 00:15:05,911
I got a whole bunch of lands,
put the creatures down--

514
00:15:05,911 --> 00:15:06,977
- And Sierra, you, same thing.

515
00:15:06,977 --> 00:15:08,084
You were getting no creatures, right?

516
00:15:08,084 --> 00:15:09,026
And when you did get one,

517
00:15:09,026 --> 00:15:12,439
we would attack 
and you'd lose them all.

518
00:15:12,439 --> 00:15:13,568
Anyway, so you 
guys are good, then?

519
00:15:13,568 --> 00:15:14,741
- Yeah, I like it.

520
00:15:14,741 --> 00:15:15,970
- Alright, cool, I'm excited.

521
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:17,049
They just need more practice.

522
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:19,916
It's a game that takes
time to learn the skill

523
00:15:19,916 --> 00:15:20,816
and what all the things do

524
00:15:20,816 --> 00:15:22,003
and when to use them.

525
00:15:22,003 --> 00:15:23,397
But even just 
in that second game,

526
00:15:23,397 --> 00:15:24,748
you guys were definitely
picking things up.

527
00:15:24,748 --> 00:15:25,998
So I'm excited.

528
00:15:27,946 --> 00:15:29,504
Well, guys, this is the way
we're gonna end the vlog,

529
00:15:29,504 --> 00:15:30,446
hope you enjoyed it.

530
00:15:30,446 --> 00:15:32,209
Unfortunately, like I said,

531
00:15:32,209 --> 00:15:34,218
kind of epic fail when it
came to going and looking

532
00:15:34,218 --> 00:15:35,051
at dirt bikes today,

533
00:15:35,051 --> 00:15:36,760
but like I said,

534
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,525
when we get back 
from our trip this week,

535
00:15:38,525 --> 00:15:39,797
we'll definitely go back out,

536
00:15:39,797 --> 00:15:42,378
hit up a couple more shops
that were closed today,

537
00:15:42,378 --> 00:15:44,016
and we will make 
our final decision

538
00:15:44,016 --> 00:15:46,683
on a new dirt bike 
for the kids.

539
00:15:48,576 --> 00:15:49,851
This is our 
last-ditch effort, really.

540
00:15:49,851 --> 00:15:52,720
We buy this new bike, 
a new four-stroke,

541
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:55,222
and if they don't 
get the confidence,

542
00:15:55,222 --> 00:15:56,943
they don't feel like riding,

543
00:15:56,943 --> 00:15:58,776
it might be the last dirt
bike the kids ever own.

544
00:15:58,776 --> 00:16:01,413
But, speaking of 
dirt bikes, tomorrow

545
00:16:01,413 --> 00:16:03,580
Mike Junior Swag hit us up

546
00:16:04,487 --> 00:16:05,840
and wants to go 
ride in the morning,

547
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:06,864
so I'm gonna 
go riding with them

548
00:16:06,864 --> 00:16:08,543
in the morning bright and early,

549
00:16:08,543 --> 00:16:10,595
so stay tuned tomorrow, 
dirt bike video.

550
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:13,000
Whoo, vlog on.

About Baby Alive Dolls and Toys AKA Baby Alive Channel
My name is Heather and I'm a mother to 4 beautiful and fun kids.  You'll sometimes see my kids Maddy, Elsie, Jake and Beau in our videos.  We love making family friendly videos for kids of all ages.  We love dolls of all kinds.  Some of the dolls you'll see us unbox and play with are Baby Alive Dolls,  Lol Surprise Dolls, American Girl Bitty Baby Dolls, Cabbage Patch Kids, My Life As, Our Generation,  My Sweet Love, You & Me, Barbie, American Girl Wellie Wisher, Baby Born and Water Babies just to name a few.  Its so important to me to make sure my kids have clean family/kid friendly safe content to watch, so I can assure you that you'll never see us make videos that are teaching anything but good.  I always try to teach positive lessons in my videos.  We hope you enjoy watching our videos.

title: The Hard Lives of Britain's Synthetic Marijuana Addicts
description:
Legal highs are set to be outlawed by the British government in response to a growing number of news reports about students overdosing on the synthetic drugs after using them recreationally. On the eve of the ban, VICE travelled to Manchester to meet some more vulnerable users who have become addicted to these over-the-counter substances and discovered that solving the problem won't be as simple as making legal highs illegal. 

Watch the newest VICE feature on Fentanyl, The Drug Deadlier than Heroin: http://bit.ly/2aB2Ead

World's Scariest Drug: http://bit.ly/1MpY7GI

Teenage Heroin Epidemic: http://bit.ly/1gQ9L0D


Click here to subscribe to VICE: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-VICE

Check out our full video catalog: http://bit.ly/VICE-Videos
Videos, daily editorial and more: http://vice.com
More videos from the VICE network: https://www.fb.com/vicevideos

Follow us on Instagram: http://instagram.com/vice
Check out our Pinterest: https://pinterest.com/vicemag

We're Teagan & Sam and we post videos to Squared every Monday!  If you're wondering, we're from Australia!

title: DIY Heart Friendship Bracelets
description:
This Friendship bracelet tutorial shows how to DIY heart friendship bracelets. These DIY bracelets are really easy, simple, but cute and I show how to make them step by step, slowly for beginners. To make one of these cute heart bracelets you need embroidery floss, string or a thread and a cute button. We will make an awesome DIY button ending to this heart friendship bracelet, which will allow us to take the bracelet on and off our wrist without damaging it. You can use any color you would like to make these bracelets to match your outfit, so these bracelets are always fashionable. You can wear these DIY heart friendship bracelets alone or you can pair them with other bracelet jewelry. They go great with either gold or silver bracelets. These bracelets are a great gift and perfect for Valentines Day! If you use darker colors perhaps these bracelets can be worn by men (your boyfriend) or you can make it for your best friend. I have made three heart bracelets just for me!

http://sarabeautycorner.com/

We need four pieces of string for this heart friendship bracelet DIY. We pull strings together, make a knot in the middle of the bracelet and tape strings to a flat surface. Then we start to knot and to make a heart friendship bracelet we need to know how to make two different knotting rows -- a normal and a special friendship bracelet rows. For that, we need to learn how to make two knots -- a forward and a backward knot. Then we just continue with rows, two special and two normal until the heart friendship bracelet is long enough to fit around our wrist. This is all there is to this easy for beginners friendship bracelet DIY.

In this friendship bracelet tutorial I show how to make a heart pattern. If you would like me to make other friendship bracelet patterns, like a chevron friendship bracelet, let me know in the comments and I may do another bracelet DIY. It will be just as easy, perfect for bracelet making beginners.

Help me translate this DIY: https://www.youtube.com/timedtext_video?v=pfjfikSEVM8

Become my Friend & Enter Giveaways :)

description:

Don't miss the HOTTEST NEW TRAILERS: http://bit.ly/1u2y6pr

CLIP DESCRIPTION:
Cher (Alicia Silverstone) and Dionne (Stacey Dash) talk on their cell phones while walking down the hall; Cher tells about her mother.

FILM DESCRIPTION:
Jane Austen might never have imagined that her 1816 novel Emma could be turned into a fresh and satirical look at ultra-rich teenagers in a Beverly Hills high school. Cher (Alicia Silverstone) and Dionne (Stacey Dash), both named after "great singers of the past that now do infomercials," are pampered upper-class girls who care less about getting good grades than wearing the right clothes and being as popular as possible. But Cher, who lives with her tough yet warm-hearted lawyer dad (Dan Hedaya) and hunky, sensitive stepbrother (Paul Rudd), also has an innate urge to help those less fortunate -- like the two introverted teachers she brings together ("negotiating" herself improved grades in the process) and new friend Tai (Brittany Murphy), who starts out a geek and ends up a Cher prodigy. Cher also possesses her own sensitive side, and she is looking for the perfect boyfriend, whom she ends up finding where she least expected.
